<pre><center><img src="/esoup/gif/barfrac1.gif" align=bottom width=555 height=17></center></pre>
<pre><a name="Two Peas in a Pod"><STRONG>Two Peas in a Pod</STRONG></a><STRONG>
     by Andres Duran
	 Andres is a third grader at Robert Hunter.
	 This story is about his best friend, Kevin Mc Nutt.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     Once there was a boy named Andres who liked school.  One day 
he met a boy who liked school, too.  This boy's name was Kevin.  
Kevin and Andres both liked sports like football, basketball, 
hockey, and soccer.
     One day Kevin broke a window.  When someone was going to tell,
Andres said, &quot;Wait, I broke the window.  I'll pay for it.  I 
promise.&quot;  So they walked to school.
     One day Andres was getting picked on.  Kevin said to the 
bully, &quot;Hey, why don't you pick on someone your own size?&quot;  
     Andres said, &quot;Thanks,&quot; to Kevin.
     Later that day Kevin told Andres that he was moving.  Andres 
asked Kevin why.  Kevin told Andres that his father had a new job 
in Ohio, and he would be moving next week.
     The week passed by fast.  Andres was sad all the time.  
Just as Andres thought Kevin was gone, the doorbell rang.  
It was Kevin.  Kevin said, &quot;I didn'tmove because of you.&quot;  
     Andres answered, &quot;You are the best.&quot;
			     </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><br>
<br>
<img src="/esoup/gif/balloon2.gif" align=bottom width=32 height=32></STRONG><a href="#Young Writers"><STRONG>Return to Young Writers Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
