<html>

<head>
<title>Electric Soup Poetry</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Vermeer FrontPage 1.0">
</head>

<body background="/esoup/gif/blueblob.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#004000">
<h1><a name="Poetry"><U>Electric Soup</U> Poetry</a></h1>
<p><STRONG>Adrienne Rich is a poet, feminist thinker, and political<br>
activist. She sees a power in words and art when she<br>
states, &quot;Poetry can bring together those parts of us which <br>
exist in dread.&quot; </STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/frjenry.jpg" align=bottom width=358 height=234><br>
--Jennifer Schneiderman, Freqerique, de Lame, and Ryan Miller: Poetry Editors</STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG>Pieces in this volume include: </STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#foaming anguish"><STRONG>Foaming Anguish</STRONG></a><STRONG> by Ryan Miller </STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#bird"><STRONG>Bird</STRONG></a><STRONG> by Laura Kuznicki</STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Thinking as a Child"><STRONG>Thinking as a Child</STRONG></a><STRONG> by Heather Wyatt </STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#freedom from myself"><STRONG>Freedom from Myself</STRONG></a><STRONG> by Kristina Sutphen </STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#firefly"><STRONG>Haiku: Firefly</STRONG></a><STRONG> by Mimi Pare </STRONG></p>
