<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<pre><a name="foaming anguish"><STRONG>Foaming Anguish</STRONG></a></pre>
<pre><STRONG>Again the foamy green waves
Spill up on the empty beachline
Footprints pressed in the sand
Have long been washed away.
The smell in the air, pleasing
To the broken hearts which lay
Half sunken in the millions
Of shattered shell bits.
And the gulls gently floating overhead
Swooping down to pick at the remaing
Seaweed that was once a person's soul
And is now being brought in by the tide.
</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          -Ryan Miller

</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<pre><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/laurak2.jpg" align=right width=175 height=144></STRONG><a name="bird"><STRONG>BIRD</STRONG></a><STRONG>
</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>I stand high and spread my vast wings
     Light uncovered, a new day is born
Perched high in glory, I see the world
     The wind blows for me, it is all mine</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>Darkness comes and my wings grow weak
     I can no longer bear to hold the weight
So I let it all fall down on my  body
     And I feel the night beginning to set</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>My eyes slowly shut and my heart closes down
     There is a certain peace in the air
I can feel the tranquility run through my blood
     And I know that life will be fine</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>The sun rises and again my wings are spread
     Sweet morning air touches my lungs
I stand back on my spot, my rock, my home
     And realize again that I am free
</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                         -Laura Kuznicki
</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<pre><a name="Thinking as a Child"><STRONG>Thinking as a Child</STRONG></a></pre>
<pre><STRONG>I wonder what it's like to know that
silliness is a way of life
or that balloon men really do charge
outrageously.
I wonder what it would be like to talk out-
loud in a sullen library
or swim in the rain spouting overhead.
I wonder what I could do with myself if I
wasn't a captive of fauvism
or a stunning romantic.
I wonder what it would be like to see after
many years of being frozen
or capturing more than one butterfly in a
silk trap.
I wonder why I only want to become one
certain person 
or try to begin a life I never had.
I wonder who I'd marry when I become old
enough to believe in commitment
or if I'd ever become hopelessly lonely.
I wonder what people are doing at this
exact moment
or do I really want to know.
I wonder why reading is such a bother for
some people but a journey for others
or why I  can't write a novel of my own.
I wonder how beginnings and endings will
look at age 76
or why people stand still to look at art.
I wonder if one day I will ever see the hunt
being hunted or 
cry at every tearful movie in front of my
family.
I wonder who I dream about every night and 
if his eyes are a deadly night shade.
I wonder what I don't know that won't hurt
me
and what is being intellectual sexy.
I wonder if I will ever see my only brother
marry someone who will clean after him or
if I will dance with him at my own wedding
reception.
I wonder if I will ever look at things the
same way or
will everything I've seen and worked for
change.
I wonder if I will ever be truly happy 
or if I will just pretend to be.
			 -Heather Wyatt</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<pre><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/sutphen.jpg" align=right width=184 height=190></STRONG><a name="freedom from myself"><STRONG>Freedom From Myself</STRONG></a></pre>
<pre><STRONG>I never felt so empty, as empty as I did.
I betrayed you;
I left you stranded.
I was not the friend you were.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>You found me all alone, 
You sheltered me from the cold.
You rescued me from lonely bitterness, 
I had known so well.   I needed you.
You were my blanket in the cold,
You were a hand to hold in the darkness.
You were everything that I could have asked for.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>Now, the table has turned, and you're the one hiding.
Although my words of sorrow and guilt seem to comfort you,
I am still empty inside.
I can't help knowing I don't know how you feel.
I don't know what you are thinking.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>We are two, different people.
You sheltered me from not just my fears, but my problems.
However, I never learned how to cope, 
Or how to help.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>That is why I am lonely still.
Even though I am rescued,
I'm rescued from myself, not the real stuff,
Just the pretty pictures, and the fake, smiling face.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>I am not real.    You see the mask,
The blanket that once sheltered me.
They have become my life and my light.
I don't know how to feel or what it is like to feel.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>I haven't cared in so long.
I can't stop myself from my imagining.
All I see is you sheltering me.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>I don't know how to save you from your dreams,
Or quiet the storm.
But still,  I must thank you.
You rescued me from myself and freed my soul. 
		    -Kristina Sutphen
</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<pre><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></pre>
<pre></pre>
<pre><a name="firefly"><STRONG>Firefly-</STRONG></a><STRONG>
Lost lightning
flashing to find the others.
</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>-Mimi Pare 
</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<pre><STRONG>                </STRONG><a name="when you left"><STRONG> When You Left   </STRONG></a><STRONG>          </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/magnatta.jpg" align=right width=230 height=173>I lay in a fetal position
       paralyzed by reality
Silence would be the sound
       if my mind wasn't yelling at my heart
Communication is virtually unoccupied
Loneliness spreads through my body
       like wax down a non dripless candle</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>Crimson roses dry out on my dresser
       with a stolen note
Slowly one by one
I eat the petals
       swallowing an unforgettable recollection of
my past</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>Sheets are ripped from my bed
Nightmares of love
       always leave me drowning in the ocean of you
Though I'm a fish     I can't swim
</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                           -Leigh Anne Magnatta
</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<pre><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/rking.jpg" align=right width=209 height=208></STRONG><a name="dry"><STRONG>DRY</STRONG></a><STRONG>
				</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>Now I'm stranded-
And trapped in love.
Thoughts evolving  into pain.
I  think to myself,
       bleed myself,
	    cry myself to sleep.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>Transluscent hearts in all of you-
Everyone is emotionless.
Neither pushing me, nor pulling me,
       leaving me alone.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>I run as far as life will let me- 
       It's love that makes me
Want to see the end of life-
       To hide away from everyone's sight-
To see my own way.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>I'll run to the end-
       Jump and fall,
My heart will break,
       and I'll never love him again.
</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>-Robyn King</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<pre><STRONG>                    
</STRONG><a name="Life Analogy"><STRONG>Life Analogy #3:
Gertz's Post-Dinner Party</STRONG></a><STRONG>
		    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                    
		    It's late at night
		    and here we are
		    staring at the TV,
		    laughing at space ghost.
		    Drunk on
		    lack of sleep,
		    kinship,
		    and mountain dew.
		    During a commercial
		    I stop and think.
		    It's then that I know
		    this time
		    is one of the
		    good times,
		    but like all good times,
		    it will end in the morning.
		    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                    
		      -M.Russell
		    </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a><STRONG> </STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<p><img src="/esoup/gif/hornstei.jpg" align=left width=195 height=222></p>
<h4><a name="the sun shines"><STRONG>the sun shines</STRONG></a><STRONG>--by Sarah Hornstein</STRONG></h4>
<pre><STRONG>the sun shines
but where i am
it's raining.
		    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>he says to the child,
&quot;it's time to go to bed.&quot;
Child replies, &quot;it's time 
you let me make my 
Own Decisions.&quot;
		    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>               Woman cries, &quot;It's my Life!
		    Let me live it!&quot;
		    Mind replies, &quot;You belong 
		    to me. And i decide.&quot;
		    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                    Puppy-dog barks, &quot;Run, cat,
		    Run!&quot;
		    Kitty-cat hisses, &quot;I'll bite
		    your nose!&quot;
		    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                    Junkie of beauty, slave to the
		    mirror screams, &quot;I am not Pretty!
		    I am not Pretty!&quot;
		    The gorgeous one replies,
		    &quot;You're
		    not me.&quot;
		    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                    i sit and Listen, listening
		    and weeping inside. Writing
		    and Watching and 
		    Taking In.
		    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                    There is no reality.
		    There is no Time.
		    There is no me.
		    I've crossed the line.

		    To Dreamland.
				      </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a><STRONG> </STRONG></p>
<pre><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG>
<STRONG>                    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>         </STRONG><a name="Rose Untouched"><STRONG> Rose Untouched</STRONG></a><STRONG>
	 </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          The clouds rolling in.
	  The sun peering silently from between the hills.
	  The moon setting within the light, not seen.
	  Blackness rolls in.
	  Suddenly I am engulfed in darkness.
	  I close my petals to shelter myself.
	  During the night of black, I hear the quiet pittering of rain
	  drops.
	  But then I am enclosed in coldness.
	  Will I return from this freezing madness?
	  And suddenly I am awakened by the light and heat of the
	  sun.
	  I expose myself to the world.
	  I watch my fellow flowers open petal by petal.
	  Suddenly I see shoes, deafening with every step.
	  I pray, please, not me.
	  The listless blades held tightly by her pale stubby hands,  
	  Her gentle fingers reach imperturbablely for me.
	  My dying scream was heard by no one but me.
	  The shiny black finish of the scissors gleamed in the
	  luminous sun.
	  In one quick cut my life was brought to an end.
	  But to my surprise I awakened to find myself alive.
	  I was not whole, but alive.
	  I had been set into water, placed on display.
	  I was to live as an exhibit to all who passed to see.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                                                 -Kristen Haver
	  </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<pre><center><a name="Eternal Pump"><STRONG>Eternal Pump of Evil</STRONG></a><STRONG>
	       </STRONG></center></pre>
<pre><STRONG>               It beats, churning,
	       Turning out bile and waste.
	       The eternal pump of evil
	       Is loud enough to hear.
	       But no, your ears deceived you,
	       Your eyes lie,
	       Your mouth has a mind of its own.
	       The demonic plague of scum is taking control.
	       Ask the question, 'Are you alive?'
	       You're extinct, you don't even exist,
	       But you're alive.
	       You cannot conquer,
	       Hopeless,
	       Yet out of the woodwork,
	       A burst of sun
	       A ray of sun,
	       A bolt of good, suppressed, forever.
	       </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>               
				 -Nicholas Burns
	       </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11> </STRONG></p>
<h3><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/jack.jpg" align=bottom width=330 height=188></STRONG><a name="another day"><STRONG> Another Day in the City </STRONG></a></h3>
<pre><STRONG>     I, once again step down from the concrete stoop
     Leaving behind those lingering claps,
     Still filling my head.
     Words suspended in the air of memory.
     Sigh with contentment, seeing my pride
     In the dull gray of my warm breath amongst the city's
     Cold air.
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     Scarf around neck, fingers peering through gloves
     Too thin.
     In the alley across the way,
     A new mother screams of 
     Pain;  her pups emerge, soon to die.
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     Odd, I think, for a bitch to be having a litter
     In the fall.        In the death.
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     Rats scatter as I quickly trod away from this place.
     Disease, stench, garbage, dirt, all plentiful here,
     I am quick to leave the scene.
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     My numb ears hear a scream here,
     a shout there, a shot even. . .
     All regular occurrences here in the city.
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     At the corner a prostitute shoots up,
     Her only way to stand the man she will be with;
     She looks only fourteen or so - a young one.
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     My eyes drift from spot to spot,
     Alert!
     They have to be, this is the city.
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     My hand lingering in the sky, a taxi driver
     Notices me.
     Notices me. . .an unusual occurrence indeed!
     Directions shown, not spoken.
     The driver, of course, cannot understand English.
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     Overcharged, but home
     Up the steps, memories of stale beer, old smoke,
     and a microphone dancing in my head.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                         -Jack Fitzgerald
 </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a><STRONG> </STRONG></p>
<pre><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></pre>
<h3 align=center><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/confer.jpg" align=left width=201 height=151><br>
</STRONG><a name="film"><STRONG>Film </STRONG></a><STRONG><br>
</STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>     
     sucked into a new perspective 
	  new worlds of churning imagination
     a story unravels its spool of surprises 
		unpredictably
	  images woven into a pattern of thought
				the mind captured in colored filaments
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     astonished from events
	  pleasure for the eyes
     the story you never thought of 
	  shakes your hand
			 persuades you 
			      betrays you
				   and reels you in
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     a  journey, a quest in dreamy atmospheres
		    spiraling staircases, 
			 opening doors, 
		    characters of intrigue
			 a collection of faces 
		    typhoons of emotion
			 the scenes 
			      the sensations 
     escape the real world for a while
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                   -Curt Confer </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<pre><STRONG>     </STRONG><a name="life"><STRONG>Life </STRONG></a><STRONG>                         
		    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     Life is like the deep blue ocean 
     Being born on a rainy day, 
     moving and swaying in all directions, 
     getting pushed all around
     There are times when giant, angry waves 
     come crashing hard to the ground, 
     we all fall apart
     Then there are times when the kind, warm sun
     is shining bright 
     and many people come to visit 
     and enjoy our company, 
     we are happy and grateful 
     But we cannot forget death 
     when we drift up on the welcoming shore 
     and evaporate into nothing
     Life is also like a tree 
     Starting from a little seed, 
     then sprouting and growing 
     With great strong roots 
     to support us like our family 
     There are times when we are covered 
     with beautiful, bright green leaves, 
     we are handsome, warm, and feeling good
     Then there are times when we are bare 
     with no protection from the world, 
     we are miserable and confused 
     We age for many years, 
     then one day we start to cripple, 
     then we fall, 
     no longer living     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                         -Jacki Martin
     </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/cy_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3><a name="my path"><STRONG>MY PATH TO FATE </STRONG></a></h3>
<pre><STRONG>     blue sand settles like dust 
     across my line of fate 
     cool but crisp wind
     blows through my hair 
     leaving me refreshed 
     by scent 
     I know I have a noticeable 
     crossroad lying in front of me
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     is that my two-way trail
	  one 
	  that leads to an obvious
	  future of nowhere
     the other 
	  to a perfect destination 
     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     running in circles 
     like a headless chicken 
     exhausts me 
     to know the difference 
     between the two is virtually impossible 
     time is running short 
     and I don't know which way to turn
     if I stand on my line of fate 
     will the blue sand smother me
     should I attempt to cross my line 
     or should I pick a path
     and take it
     better yet 
     I'll create my own path
     and follow it to the end     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>               -Marissa Marianino
     </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Poetry"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a><STRONG> </STRONG></p>
