<pre><center><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/laurak.jpg" align=left width=190 height=181></STRONG></center></pre>
<h3 align=center><a name="Mall Madness, Part 5"><STRONG>Mall Madness, Part 5</STRONG></a><STRONG> <br>
New continuation by Laura Kuznicki</STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>     &quot;This is getting way out of hand,  guys,&quot; 
said Sam as the teens recovered from the fright 
of the gunshot.  &quot;We need to find out where that 
noise came from, and we need this to end.  I 
have had enough of this silly game.  I can't 
take it anymore.&quot;
     &quot;Don't you see, Sam, this is not going to 
end.  I, I . . . have this feeling.  This isn't 
just a coincidence.  Someone had this planned 
for us.&quot;  Mary's voice was shakey as she tried to unravel the plot.
     Kate let out a light sob as she tried to imagine what might
become of them.  Vivid images flashed through her mind.   &quot;Guys,&quot;
she whined, &quot;I want to go home.&quot;
     &quot;There is no way that I am staying here any longer,&quot; Mike
replied in an annoyed voice.  &quot;I'll get us out of here if it kills 
me!&quot;  He started to run at an ever-quickening pace and then threw 
his body towards the glass door.  His head hit with a hard, painful
smack. Blood spilled out onto the bleached white floor.  Mike 
didn't move or speak..
     &quot;Quick, we have to help him!&quot; yelled Sam.  Sam ran over to
the motionless body of his friend and felt for a heartbeat.  
&quot;There is no pulse!&quot;  The warm, red blood covered Sam's hands as 
he started to cry.  He took off his short-sleeved tee-shirt and 
tried to wrap it around Mike's bloody skull.   It was not helping.  
They knew that there was no way to help him now.     </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>   Kate knelt down on the mall floor sobbing to herself.   Her
stomach would soon not be able to handle the sight of her friend's
blood spilled out onto the floor.  She looked up to see a strange
man standing in front of the Food Court.   He had something shiny 
in his hand.   Kate was about to alert her friends when, in a split
second, the terrible noise of a gun shot went off again.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     What do you think happens next?  Contribute your ideas in
story form!
</STRONG></pre>
