<h3><a name="Divine Intervention"><STRONG>Divine Intervention </STRONG></a></h3>
<pre><STRONG>his car door opened, 
music falling onto the pavement
in slow-motion syrupy beats 
notes dissolving on contact with 
terrestrial atmosphere.  i glimpsed briefly 
his sequin-laden earth-tone green 
leisure suit; 
mirror-black sunglasses 
and a grin of golden teeth 
from which apostles skittered to and from, 
brushing and flossing 
and clamoring for words to exaggerate 
into prophecy. 
it's all about image, he said; 
later they proclaimed his voice was thunder.
</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     -Matt Kuznicki   </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3 align=center><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/brooke.jpg" align=left width=201 height=153></STRONG><a name="Sunset"><STRONG>Sunset<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
</STRONG></a></h3>
<pre><STRONG>          the sunset was like a child's 
		coloring book-
	  colors drawn across the sky,
	  like crayons dragging softly 
		outside the lines</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          crayons are able to be used up - 
	  they dim, pale, mix, become ugly With dirt,
	  while no one can rob you of a sunset</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          sunset is when the crickets play their song,
	  and when the nocturnal ones fly in the shade
	  it means that darkness is falling
	  ironic how the clouds melt together,
	  like they are crying for the warm summer day</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          the night was made for me, it seems
	  moonlight to shine on my soul,
	  and little stars that guide fate to me
</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                         -Brooke Hennessey</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3 align=center><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/irene.jpg" align=right width=270 height=222></STRONG></h3>
<h3 align=center><a name="Memories of You"><STRONG>My Memory of You, Sir<br>
</STRONG></a></h3>
<pre><STRONG>My memory of you, Sir, is quite vague.
You should be a big part of my life, 
  but someone else loves me now.
You left, Sir,
  and your space has been filled.
I never knew why you did it,
  and I know I never will.
But I do wonder sometimes 
  about what my life would be like
  if you were in it. 
I sometimes wish you would show up one 
	day,
  but I have to be honest.
I don't know how I would act. 
Would I hit you or would I hug you?
I ask myself many questions, 
  time and time again.
Do you know that I am even here,
  or did you forget me when you ran?
I have your lips, 
  you know.
And your thick, Greek hair, Sir.
I, unfortunately, have your temper as well,
  but I never use it as a weapon. 
I only conceal one more question:
Do you still love me?
If you don't, I understand.
I can't say that I even know you, 
  but I can say this.
Maybe someday, Sir,
   you will be my father again.
</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>-Irene Pirgiotis Borkin</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3><a name="Whatever Happens"><STRONG>WHATEVER HAPPENS, HAPPENS</STRONG></a><STRONG><br>
</STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>  i never thought it would be like this
   foolish,
      irresponsible 
		  and sloppy
  her once hard body is full of ink and holes
  it reminds me of her rotting brain
  the sharp cold steel is ripping my spine apart
  causing curdled tears and blood to fall
  and in those few seconds, my dreams fled from me
  a complete deletion of the perception i once knew
  i seemed so ignorant
  no, she seemed so ignorant
  not to know how beloved her soft ancient soul was
  not to know the weapon she carried
  could destroy, 
   burn 
     and eliminate
  and so one night
  in a store full of rectangular boxes
  and a collage of pictures (so interesting to look at)
  she spoke to me in a friendly, drunken voice
  i felt like the biggest wall in the universe
  so shattered and heart broken
  and the knife kept on twisting when she had acted like nothing 
	happened
  i spied on her physical appearance
  and noticed that she had corrupted her body with alcohol 
	and fat
  her pale eyes that i once imagined as a warm, friendly 
	massive ocean
  had turned into chiseled ice
  it was the hardest thing about her
  a warm blanket of passion and ecstasy
  that i could feel flying away into a violent bliss
  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                       - jennifer witt
 </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/baker.jpg" align=left width=180 height=180></STRONG></h3>
<h3><a name="Escape"><STRONG>Escape</STRONG></a><STRONG><br>
</STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>Beyond the door of her body
Is an innocent young girl
Looking to escape
With nowhere to go.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>A beauty within her
No one can see 
Looking for someone
To open her heart</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>She's hiding, can't you see?
Her radiance is shining
Don't you wonder where?
Look, look in through her eyes.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>Her spirit is alive like a flame
Her heart is warm as a hot summer's day
She's frail on the outside, but her soul is strong
On the inside she's like a fierce lion, trying to escape.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>Sensitivity, caring, are traits of hers
Be careful, don't scare her, she'll run away
She wants to break through, and will,
Someday.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>She's ready to escape and show herself
Stand up to anything, so they know she's alive
Now, come on, do it
Escape! Escape! Escape!
 </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>               - Nicole Baker
</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/albrecht.jpg" align=right width=238 height=198></STRONG><a name="My Violin"><STRONG>My Violin</STRONG></a></h3>
<h3></h3>
<pre><STRONG>    Hanging on the wall
    shining under the spotlight.
    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>    Dark reds and oranges and yellows
    collaborate to create 
    a warmth of their own.
    The steel,
    cold and glistening,
    emits a sound so sweet and pleasing 
	to the ear.
    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>    Ebony blending with maple,
    age mixing with sound.
    </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>    My violin 
    hanging on the wall.
    </STRONG></pre>
<h3><STRONG>-Christina Albrecht</STRONG></h3>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3 align=center><a name="Night Falls"><STRONG>Night Falls</STRONG></a></h3>
<pre><STRONG>          Night falls,
	  And the dark sets in.
	  But darkness is nothing new to me.
	  I've lived my whole life in the dark, 
	  Waiting for that light called
	  &quot;Happiness&quot;
	  To shine on me.
	  But that dark rain cloud above my head
	  Never leaves,
	  Never allows even a shaft of light to get
	  through.
	  And so I sit,
	  Alone,
	  Wanting,
	  Wishing,
	  Yet always just a spectator.
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                        -Dana Bivona</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/mcnam.jpg" align=right width=174 height=154></STRONG><a name="Forgery"><STRONG>Forgery </STRONG></a><STRONG><br>
<br>
<br>
</STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>          
	  I don't know you, do you know me?
	    You're not the person you seem to be.
	  You lie to all the world,
	    You're not the perfect little girl.
	  Why do you pretend to be
	    the person they all want to see?
	  You're just like a doll seen at the store,
	    pretty face- nothing more.
	  You don't always have to pretend,
	    will your charade ever end?
	  You try to keep it all inside,
	    I know you too well, you cannot hide.
	  You put on a happy face,
	     and pretend the world's a perfect place.
	  Whatever happens you don't seem to
	  care,
	    you're like a child's teddy bear-
	  on the outside you're all sweetness and
	  fluffing,
	   on the inside you're nothing but stuffing.
	  I wish, just for once, you could be true,
	   but I know better than to expect that
	  from you.  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                            -Anne McNamara
</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3 align=center><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/chun.jpg" align=left width=185 height=186></STRONG></h3>
<h3 align=center><a name="Changes"><STRONG>Changes</STRONG></a></h3>
<h3></h3>
<pre><STRONG>          Changes
	  Chubby crayons, 
		  clutched in a chubby hand, 
		  soon to be replaced by number
	  two pencils.
	  A medium of finger paints
		   to be abandoned for computer
	  graphics.
	  Playdough left for clay.
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          Climbing trees forgotten 
		  for climbing corporate ladders.
	  Curling up beside your mother 
		  given up for loud, frantic
	  outbursts of anger.
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          Dandelions left as weeds.
	  Shiny stickers and butterflies
	  neglected 
		  for less simplistic materials.
	  Naive love gone,
		   and in its place sarcasm.
	  Joy replaced by want.
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                            -Debbi Chun </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3><a name="Corner"><STRONG>Corner</STRONG></a><STRONG><br>
</STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>          
	  Go ahead and sear your sordid
	  symphony across my face,
	  I'll not speak,
	  I'll not let my throat scratch out the
	  harmful melody,
	  I'll not command you to cease with
	  an angry hand...
	  I'll not wake.
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          I'll not flee the forgettable fire which
	  always ensues,
	  The struggle which has always been
	  beneath you,
	  Behind closed doors and heavy
	  darkness
	  I'll not cry,
	  For you have ceased to move me.
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          I shall forget the heavy beat which
	  you pursue,
	  Disguisor,
	  Leave off the acid apology,
	  You do not trick me, cannot fool me,
	  cannot hide,
	  You insult me more than your thick
	  cigarette smoke
	  Scrambling away in dark gulps,
	  As I do.
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          Go ahead and take another drag,
	  I watch your breath burn as the
	  cigarette burns ashes and
	  Hope.
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                      -Carolyn Chun
	  </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/sutphen.jpg" align=right width=184 height=190></STRONG><a name="struggle"><STRONG>struggle</STRONG></a><STRONG><br>
</STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>          i am
	  Like a candle in the wind
	  With its flame running
	  The wick getting shorter
	  Wax melting
	  The fight to stay lit
	  Like a bird without a nest
	  Scared
	  Without words
	  I flicker
	  The blaze starts to sizzle
	  Bursting with heat
	  And I wonder,
	  If really,
	  i am
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                  -Kristina Sutphen</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<pre><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></pre>
<h3><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/guerra.jpg" align=left width=256 height=232></STRONG><a name="Time"><STRONG>TIME </STRONG></a></h3>
<pre><STRONG>          How I've longed for peace of mind
	  Or a minute to unwind
	  Life's too fast to stop
	  And too busy to be kind
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          
	  It isn't much that I ask
	  Forget the horrors of the past
	  Still one thing can comfort me
	  Time will set the memory free
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          
	  For it is the memory that haunts me
	  Keeps me up at night
	  It lurks beneath the shadows
	  And crawls beside the night
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          
	  It's his dark grasp that holds me
	  Forbids me to stay here
	  Locked inside the shadows
	  Deep inside my fears
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          
	  So as I sit and ask you why
	  don't hide the tears that make you cry
	  Tell me how and tell me why 
	  He must suffer and slowly die
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>                             -Deron Guerra</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<pre><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></pre>
<h3><a name="Wish I could"><STRONG>Wish I could</STRONG></a><STRONG> </STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>          wish i could
	       go on pretending
	       ignore what you ve become
	       be what i m not
	       say that this smile on display is real
	       say that everything is okay
	       continue waiting
	       say that i have more to give you
	       kill away all the anger
	       numb myself a little more
	       push just a little harder
	       stop the bleeding
	       neglect you
	       have stopped myself from meeting you
	       kill you
	       forget you
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>               i wish i could say that i don t love you
	  </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>          wish i could
	       but i can't.
			 -Carl Weeks</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<pre><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/gr_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11>          </STRONG></pre>
<h3><a name="The Blizzard"><STRONG>The Blizzard </STRONG></a><STRONG><br>
</STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>The snow won't stop falling from up high in the sky.
I'm a little worried how my dad is going to fly.
He's thousands of miles away in Florida in fear.
I bet that he's worried that we are trapped here.
As my friend and I sit in the truck and plow,
My father wonders how we are doing right now.
He hears on the news that we had 35 inches,
Though we plowed it away without any flinches.
His flight was the only one scheduled for today.
Otherwise he'd be stuck there till May.
He called us to tell us he's on his way home.
And that is the end of this wonderful poem.</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>         -Jerry George        </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/purbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Top"><STRONG>Return to Poetry Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
