<h1 align=center><a name="philosophical essays"><STRONG>Electric Soup</STRONG></a><STRONG> Philosophical Essays</STRONG></h1>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/alarm.jpg" align=right width=279 height=195>Pieces in this volume include: </STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/blackbal.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20></STRONG><a href="#Rain"><STRONG>How Can Rain Become an Uplifting Occurrence?</STRONG></a><STRONG> by Jessica Terrizzi </STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/blackbal.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20></STRONG><a href="#date"><STRONG>How to Date a Woman</STRONG></a><STRONG> by Ryan Muir</STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG>Return to </STRONG><a href="esv5toc.html"><STRONG>Volume 5 Main Menu<br>
</STRONG></a><STRONG><br>
<br>
</STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/bl_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/terrizzi.jpg" align=left width=194 height=116></STRONG><a name="Rain"><STRONG>How Can Rain Become an Uplifting Occurrence?</STRONG></a><STRONG><br>
by Jessica Terrizzi</STRONG></p>
<pre><STRONG>I'm singin' in the rain, just singin' in the rain. 
What a glorious feeling I'm happy again,
I'm laughing at clouds so dark up above,
The sun's in my heart and I'm ready for love.
					By Arthur Freed

</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     Unscientifically speaking, rain is a thrilling spectacle.  
Depending upon certain uncontrollable weather conditions, droplets 
of water come gushing out of  swollen clouds.  As these drops of 
water hit welcoming surfaces, a unique melody is played to those 
willing to listen.  When free time is available to observe this 
awesome spectacle, hypnosis can occur and result in total 
relaxation.  Thunder and lighting add special effects, making 
simple showers become scary spine chilling productions of nature's 
power.  Goose bumps run through our bodies producing a strange 
feeling of excited joy. Even it its simplest form, rain stimulates 
feelings of enchantment. The steady downpour of water is a 
memorizing phenomena of nature which uplifts spirits and allows 
the mind to enter a fun-filled world of fantasy.
     Many times, however, depression occurs as black skies begin to
roll in.  The blockage of sunlight by huge dismal clouds, sets in
somber tones of sadness.  Aches and pains also begin to act up. 
Schedules are disrupted and lives altered because of this annoying
occurrence.  It is looked upon as a nuisance and wished away. 
     Rain, however, is not a nuisance.  It is essential to our 
survival and needs to be appreciated.  The first step towards 
gaining an appreciation for something is to recognize its purpose.  
By doing this, insight is gained on events which transpire.  
Events which seemed to occur for no apparent reason will become 
obvious.  This discovered information will aid in your respect of 
this occurrence.  Understanding rain's objective(s) will further 
aid in your quest of appreciating this common incident.  Clarifying 
its goal, in your mind, will help you to comprehend its systematic 
method. 
     Becoming its friend will further add to your new found
understanding of this natural phenomena.  To become rain's friend,
you must spend time with it.  The next time it rains, find an 
umbrella and pretend you are Gene Kelly.  You'll be amazed at how 
much fun you have.  After thoroughly enjoying yourself, you will 
begin looking forward to rain because it gives you an excuse to 
dance in the streets.  Your heart will be full of glee as your mind 
creates scenes from &quot;Singing in the Rain.&quot;
     Lastly, it is crucial that once you have become acquainted with
this spectacular event, you sit and observe it from freshly informed
perspective.  Your spirit will be dancing as your mind begins to
peacefully doze.  Your achieved appreciation for this event will 
stay with you as long as you allow it to flourish within your soul.  
     In conclusion, rains gloomy images are enhanced due to the
intense lives of the public.  Various demands cause numerous
distractions from life's simple pleasures.  The picture perfect world,
full of life and color, which nature has created often goes unseen.
With a great emphasis placed upon materialistic items in today's
world, many people tend to ignore nature and fail to recognize its
powerful influence.  Becoming wrapped up in the black and white
world of the economy and its industrial aspects of surviving is 
accomplished without effort.  It's necessary to step back, so the
uniqueness of this world can be appreciated.  
       Rain can be appreciated in numerous ways.  It should not be
looked upon as a dreary miserable happening that causes aches and
pains.  Instead, it should be thought of as an awesome occurrence
which nature provides to enhance the beauty of our planet.  Each
person will arrive at a personal level of appreciation when rain
begins to be viewed as a remarkable spectacle, rather than a
nuisance.  Feelings of peace to the spirits within each person's soul,
will be achieved as events in nature are viewed from a positive
perspective.  Rain occurs when enough pressure builds up inside the
clouds that they just burst.  Basically, the intense sun soaks up 
water droplets form numerous, abundant sources.  These magnetic 
droplets quickly cling together.  As one, the millions of water 
molecules represent a densely saturated sponge.  As more and more 
tiny moist particles try to squeeze into an already sated sponge, 
water slowly begins seeping out.  What began as inconstant blobs 
soon become frequent drips, which quickly transform into a steady 
leak.  With the aid of favorable natural forces, the sponge will 
eventually be squeezed dry. As beads tumble from the sky, they 
generously water the earth with life.  
       Even though rain allows life to exist, many dread rainy days. 
Various reasons cause people to despise rain, the most common
being the damp, dark, dismal curtain it drops before our eyes. 
Nevertheless, a few days of darkness is a small price to pay for the
survival of our unique planet.  It is necessary to look past the dreary
image which rain portrays.  The true beauty of rain is not seen by
looking at its outward appearance, but rather found inside its ugly
protective shell.  Each droplet of water holds within something very
special.  It carefully delivers its priceless gift to the thirsty 
terrain by means of thoughtful explosion upon impact.  By 
understanding the purpose of rain, its &quot;depressing&quot; effect will 
soon cease.  Try to think of each rain pellet as tiny spherical 
drops not only filled with water, but also with the precious gift 
of life.</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/blackbal.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20></STRONG><a href="#philosophical essays"><STRONG>Return to Philosophical Essays Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/bl_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11> </STRONG></p>
<h3><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/girl.jpg" align=left width=93 height=165></STRONG><a name="date"><STRONG>How to Date a Woman</STRONG></a><STRONG> -- by Ryan Muir <img src="/esoup/gif/muir.jpg" align=right width=133 height=125></STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>   &quot;It sure is hard to get a good date.&quot;
				-Brad Muir</STRONG></pre>
<pre></pre>
<pre><STRONG>   There is nothing in life that can 
create as many mixed emotions in a man as 
a woman.  Between the careless flippant
remark that she tosses your way, meant as 
a joke, and the long passionate kisses, 
hopefully not meant as a joke,  a person's emotions get tugged at 
and pulled on so much, it feels like men are no more than puppets.  
The situation where this is most apparent is not one of those already 
long term relationships, or marriage. Instead, as we all know, it 
shines forth in all of its beauty in the process of dating.  Whether 
it is the infamous blind-date, or just a typical dinner and a movie, 
it is a guarantee that an extremely wide range of emotions will 
present themselves.  All in all, dating a woman can be one of the most
embarrassing, frightening, and yet rewarding experiences that anyone 
could imagine.
       Before the actual date itself,  the problem of finding a woman
exists.  Now, there are literally thousands of possibilities open 
to the seeking male, so the choice can be a difficult one.  
Initially, beauty is considered.  This is done by the person 
asking himself, &quot;Can I see myself kissing her.&quot;  If the answer is 
no, continue searching on until the answer is yes.  
       Once this first requirement is met, initial contact must be
established.  Different people will go about this in different ways. 
From the famous, &quot;What's your sign, baby?&quot;  to only looking and
sharing secret smiles with each other, establishing contact can be
done in an infinite amount of ways.    One of the easiest ways to
initiate contact is to comment on a subject of common interest, such
as ( but only if nothing else is available) the weather.  The 
weather is something that both people notice and feel.  Once the 
initial, &quot;Boy, it sure is nice out today,&quot; is out, it is hard to 
believe how much easier it is to talk to each other.
       After  speaking to the woman comes the hard part, actually
asking her out on a date.  Some people will ask after only the first
few minutes, some will wait almost their whole lives.  The best plan
is not to jump into it too fast, but if the O.K. signals are present,
such as if she hasn't run screaming away or isn't in the process of
physically beating you, asking her out on a date after two or three
conversations is probably  acceptable.
       Once the right time is figured out, comes the really tough part,
getting up the nerve to actually ask.  Unknown to most women, this
is the part that men dread.  The fear of getting rejected is so bad
that our palms are sweaty, our voices are shaky, and in all 
probability, we will have to go to the bathroom right afterwards 
because of all the excitement.  This part must be overcome.  
The fear cannot be allowed to overcome our desire to date, least 
there never be a dating option again.  
       Now that the tough part is out of the way, it must be decided
where to go.  This part is usually established before the asking,  
to have eliminated as much awkwardness as possible.  Common
interests must be found and leapt upon.  Also, it should be
something unique to yourself, not something that anyone could do. 
Too many guys have asked their interest to the &quot;dinner and movie&quot;
combo, and have been rejected on the spot.  Instead, try to be
creative.  Ask the woman to do something like sledding, ice-skating,
going to a play, or something similarly interesting.  This will make
them think that you're a really cool guy, who likes to do neat things.
       Now that the woman, the activity, and the interest have all 
been decided, it is finally time to go on the date.  The first 
aspect of the date itself is what to wear.  Depending on the 
activity planned, dress should be casual yet neat.  Nothing too 
fancy.  Anything that would draw attention away from you and 
towards your clothes should be avoided; remember, you want your 
date to pay attention to you, not your shirt.  The reverse is also 
true.  Never, never dress too casual either.  There is nothing that
can spoil a date like showing up in dirty, ragged, sagging sweat 
pants and your favorite flannel that has grease stains all over it.
This part of your wardrobe should remain a secret at least until 
after a year of serious dating.
       When on the date, the best way to impress the ladies is to act
yourself.  Trying to be funny, in reality, just makes you look like
the nervous and stupid fool you are.  On the other hand, being too
serious can be a problem, too.  A woman will instantly cross off any
guy that she doesn't think that she can have a good time with. 
Instead, just like everything, a happy medium must be met. 
Hopefully, your normal personality consists of a little humor, a 
little seriousness, and immense charm.  This should be enough for 
any woman.
       The final part of the evening is the after-date kiss.  This 
is the important part.  It has been on your mind all night.  It 
has been on her mind all night.  You know that she knows that 
you've been thinking about it, and she knows that you know that 
she's been thinking about it.  It can be confusing.  This one has 
to be left up to the total discretion of the people on the date.  
If  the date turned out well, and both of you had a good time, 
then it would probably be all right to kiss the woman good night, 
but one can never be certain. One thing's for sure, if the kiss is 
received well, it is worth all of the trouble.  It is usually the 
man's job to initiate the first kiss, so good luck.  
       In retrospect, dating can be one of the scariest, most horrifying
experiences that anyone could ever go through.   From realizing the
initial interest and establishing the first conversation, to planning
where to go and what to wear, to the total indecision of the
horrifying good-night kiss,  putting your pride on the line and asking
someone out takes a lot of nerve.  But when done right, and with the
right person, the rewards can be worthwhile.  </STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/blackbal.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20></STRONG><a href="#philosophical essays"><STRONG>Return to Philosophical Essays Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG>Return to </STRONG><a href="esv5toc.html"><STRONG>Volume 5 Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
</body>

