<h1 align=center><a name="Collaborative Short Stories"><STRONG>Electric Soup</STRONG></a><STRONG> Collaborative Short Stories</STRONG></h1>
<p><STRONG>Pieces in this volume include: </STRONG></p>
<p align=center><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/comrades.jpg" align=bottom width=287 height=213> </STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Mars Federal Colony"><STRONG>Mars Federal Colony</STRONG></a><STRONG>, Part 5 -- New continuation by Topher Taylor -- Original short story 
begun by Ryan McNamara; previous episodes added by Mike Fitch, Pat Clark, and Lucy 
Robertson</STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Mall Madness"><STRONG>Mall Madness</STRONG></a><STRONG>, Part 5 -- New continuation by Desiree Carmona -- Original short story 
begun by Miriam Pare; previus episodes contributed by Nicole Baker, Meghan Bissett, and 
Laura Kuznicki (2 episodes)</STRONG></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/mimi.jpg" align=middle width=186 height=169>Return to </STRONG><a href="esv5toc.html"><STRONG>Volume 5 Main Menu</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/rd_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11> </STRONG></p>
<h3><a name="Mars Federal Colony"><STRONG>Mars Federal Colony</STRONG></a><STRONG>, Part 5 Continued by Topher Taylor<br>
</STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>     Captain Andrews' call was not returned.  He moved slowly
toward the door of his cabin.  Looking out into the hall, he saw a
bright red light.  The power must have gone out, he thought.  That
must be why Armstrong had not returned the verification.  For a
moment, Andrews forgot the tractor beam.  He was not a bright
man, and he really didn't realize the danger he was in.
     Andrews turned the corner of the hall and saw the guidance
console smashed to pieces by a large axe.  Attached to the end of
the axe was Armstrong's chest.  Scarlet oozed from the hole, barely
visible in the crimson lighting.  Andrews withdrew from the room,
not really aware of what he ought to do.  His training had
accounted for everything, or so he thought.  He thought back,
trying to recapture his training back on Earth.  He remembered
nothing of &quot;death of a crew member by a sharp object&quot; and
panicked.  Andrews ran quickly back to his quarters and fell,
sobbing, onto the bed.
     The tractor be0am finished its purpose and pulled the earth 
ship inside the alien ship.  The alien  ship was incredibly large,
approximately the size of New Jersey in area, and was manned by
almost one-million Brakazoraks.  These extraterrestrial beings had
only one purpose behind their visit to our solar system, blood. 
They had run out of a proper food source three years back, and,
man, were they hungry!
     One of the scout robots had accidentally killed one of the
humans, potential food, and the robotic scout  had, therefore,
crawled into a corner, ashamed.  The nature of these scout robots
was to destroy themselves if they were not able to follow through
with their directives, and that is precisely what this scout did 
now. 
	Unfortunately for both Andrews and the Brakazoraks, the 
corner the robot was sulking in happened to be the back corner of 
CaptainAndrews' quarters.  The robot's self-destructive explosion 
surged upon Andrews' sobbing form, tearing the flesh from his back.
He screamed loudly at the first surge.  The robot's pieces then
bombarded his body, imbedding into his flesh.  Thankfully, one of
these hit his heart, stopping it.  Tragically, Andrews was left
mangled and cold.
     Angry at the accidental deaths of the two humans, for the
Brakazoraks could only eat living flesh, the aliens decided that they
would have to visit Earth.  The Brakazoraks might have been happy
with the Mars colony's residents alone, but now they were hungry
again.  The fate of humanity lay in a questionable state . . . </STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>What do you think will occur next?  Will the crew be able to save
themselves?  Will Earth be given any warning?  How will Earth face
an alien attack?</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Collaborative Short Stories"><STRONG>Return to Collaborative Short Stories</STRONG></a></p>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/rd_bar.gif" align=bottom width=640 height=11></STRONG></p>
<h3><a name="Mall Madness"><STRONG>Mall Madness</STRONG></a><STRONG>, Part 6 New continuation by Desiree Carmona</STRONG></h3>
<pre><STRONG>     Original story begun by Miriam Pare; previous episodes
contributed by Nicole Baker, Meghan Bissett, and Laura
Kuznicki (2 episodes)</STRONG></pre>
<pre><center><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/desiree.jpg" align=bottom width=234 height=159>
</STRONG></center></pre>
<pre><STRONG>     &quot;Katie!&quot; yelled Sam as he let go of Mike's hands.
     They all ran to Kate's bloody, twisted body, but they knew 
that there was nothing they could do for her.  She was obviously 
dead from the terrible injury inflicted by the mysterious gun shot.
Now, not only were Kate and Mike dead, but the mysterious presence
who had led them to their deaths had also seemed to disappear.
     &quot;I want to leave,  Sam.  Just get me out of here, just get me
out!&quot; shrieked Mary as she collapsed crying.
     &quot;It's all right, Mary,&quot; said Sam. &quot;I'll get you out of here 
if it's the last thing I do.&quot;
     The two teens decided that the best possible thing they could 
do was to hide from the maniac, but they didn't know exactly where. 
They knew there were many good hiding spots in the mall, but they
felt like they were being watched.
     &quot;I'm getting tired of walking for so long,&quot; complained Mary.
&quot;Let's take a break.&quot;
     &quot;Okay, but make it quick.  I've got a feeling that something 
bad is going to happen,&quot; Sam said in a frightened voice.
     They began to hear those footsteps coming towards them again,
so they ran as fast as they could.  As they turned a corner, they
stopped dead in their tracks.   Their mouths dropped open in
complete horror.  There was the apparent maniac who had been
terrorizing them.  What the maniac was though they didn't know!
</STRONG></pre>
<pre><STRONG>What do Kate and Sam see?  What will happen next to the terrified
teen-agers?  You can create the next episode and submit it to 
</STRONG><STRONG><U>Electric Soup</U></STRONG><STRONG>!</STRONG></pre>
<p><STRONG><img src="/esoup/gif/redbull.gif" align=bottom width=18 height=18></STRONG><a href="#Collaborative Short Stories"><STRONG>Return to Collaborative Short Stories</STRONG></a></p>
