   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win16; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#FF8000" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" LINK="#008040" VLINK="#008040" ALINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="a154.jpg">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><A NAME="Electric Soup Community"></A><B>Electric Soup
Community </B></H1>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><B>of Writers</B></H1>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=60%><B>Volume 6 contains the following selections:</B> 
<UL>
<P><A HREF="#Taking Action"><IMG SRC="grenbull.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18></A><B><A HREF="#Taking Action">Taking
Action</A> by Florence McGinn</B></P>
</UL>

<UL>
<P><A HREF="#Before"><IMG SRC="grenbull.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18></A><B><A HREF="#Before">Before
Prayer</A> by John Livecchi</B></P>

<P><A HREF="#Maroon"><IMG SRC="grenbull.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18></A><B><A HREF="#Maroon">Maroon</A>
by John Smith</B></P>

<P><A HREF="#TOTAL MENTAL SATISFACTION"><IMG SRC="grenbull.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18></A><B><A HREF="#TOTAL MENTAL SATISFACTION">Total
Mental Satisfaction</A> by Marissa Marianino</B></P>
</UL>

<P><B>Click here to&nbsp;Return to the <A HREF="esv6toc.html">Volume 6
Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=40%><IMG SRC="blckbrd2.jpg" HEIGHT=169 WIDTH=129></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=35%><IMG SRC="fmcginn1.jpg" HEIGHT=176 WIDTH=165></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="Taking Action"></A><B>Taking Action </B>
<P><B>Florence McGinn, English Teacher </B></P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>My son stands in the secure light of childhood </B></P>

<P><B>and calls me to the orange-berried crown of thorns </B></P>

<P><B>branching its way up coarse, brown siding. </B></P>

<P><B>I nod and go to him, thinking </B></P>

<P><B>he wants me to watch baby robins, </B></P>

<P><B>freshly feathered and nested </B></P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>

<TD width=60%><B>in pyracanthra's spiney twists. </B>
<P><B>I smile, recalling the day he found </B></P>

<P><B>broken, blue shells and looked up </B></P>

<P><B>to see demanding, open mouths. </B></P>

<P><B>My son has watched strangely naked skin </B></P>

<P><B>become down and feathers. In the lid </B></P>

<P><B>of a mason jar, he has placed freshly dug, </B></P>

<P><B>fleshy earthworms to be carried aloft </B></P>

<P><B>to insistent young. He has counted </B></P>

<P><B>and frowned while five nestlings </B></P>

<P><B>slowly became two. </B></P>

<P><B>My son calls again, loudly, </B></P>

<P><B>and his arms pull at the air like a runner </B></P>

<P><B>caught in quicksand. Adult robins </B></P>

<P><B>are diving, diving at the nest. I race forward </B></P>

<P><B>to pull my boy away when I see the snake </B></P>

<P><B>winding its way up a branch, moving </B></P>

<P><B>closer to the nest, pausing only when </B></P>

<P><B>a winged parent hits its scaled body. </B></P>

<P><B>I am cold, still with the pervasive order </B></P>

<P><B>of events unfolding before our eyes. </B></P>

<P><B>But a little boy with fluttering fledglings </B></P>

<P><B>caught in the irises of his eyes, seeing wings </B></P>

<P><B>reflected in the slit irises of reptilian eyes, </B></P>

<P><B>is not obligated to accept an ordered universe, </B></P>

<P><B>a pattern of hollow gods and disintegrating suns. </B></P>

<P><B>He grabs a muddy hoe and swings it </B></P>

<P><B>with a child's awkward force, swinging </B></P>

<P><B>four times, hitting the snake twice with its blade </B></P>

<P><B>before I stop him. I can feel language </B></P>

<P><B>and time spinning outward as I watch </B></P>

<P><B>the snake slide away from the nest, </B></P>

<P><B>slide down the house foundation, </B></P>

<P><B>slide into broken azalea branches </B></P>

<P><B>and moist roots mingled with flotsam </B></P>

<P><B>of leaf layer and damp humous. </B></P>

<P><B>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Community of Writers
Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="Before"></A><B>Before Prayer </B>
<P><B>Mr. John Livecchi, English Teacher </B></P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>Boundless mystery, </B></P>

<P><B>I believe you are here and that </B></P>

<P><B>You notice me waiting in the silence. </B></P>

<P><B>I have come here to pray, hoping that </B></P>

<P><B>You welcome me. </B></P>

<P><B>Yet, every day I approach you with faltering steps; </B></P>

<P><B>Trusting that you will lead me, </B></P>

<P><B>Wanting to open myself to your possibilities </B></P>

<P><B>But frightened that you will ask too much. </B></P>

<P><B>Greed, desire and duty bind me. </B></P>

<P><B>You would free me; </B></P>

<P><B>I need only ask for my chains to fall away. </B></P>

<P><B>You offer me freedom, wholeness, pardon; </B></P>

<P><B>I depend on my faults and cares to keep us apart. </B></P>

<P><B>Help me to use my time in prayer to listen. </B></P>

<P><B>Teach me to rely on prayer as a path to you. </B></P>

<P><B>Grant me strength to forgive, to hope, to love. </B></P>

<P><B>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Community of Writers
Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="Maroon"></A><B>Maroon </B>
<P><B>Mr. John Smith, English Teacher </B></P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>I don't know about this fall. </B></P>

<P><B>Everything seems to lend itself to a burning </B></P>

<P><B>I don't think I'll survive. </B></P>

<P><B>Everywhere I go trees are on fire, </B></P>

<P><B>and I want to turn away, </B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%><IMG SRC="jsmith1.jpg" HEIGHT=123 WIDTH=182></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><B>but I'm drawn to their flames. </B><BR>
<BR>

<P><B>I don't know about this sky. </B></P>

<P><B>I've never seen such a deep, smokey blue, </B></P>

<P><B>never felt a chill as disturbing as this in the air before. </B></P>

<P><BR>
</P>

<P><B>The leaves tremble from the trees, </B></P>

<P><B>and I feel my hands shaking. </B></P>

<P><B>The wind tosses them around, </B></P>

<P><B>my thoughts swirl up and ground; </B></P>

<P><B>I can't take this breaking away anymore. </B></P>

<P><BR>
</P>

<P><B>I think the osprey I saw </B></P>

<P><B>sweeping through dusk yesterday </B></P>

<P><B>was the saddest of passings. </B></P>

<P><B>I remember last summer watching them fold in their wings </B></P>

<P><B>and surrender like prayers to the sea. </B></P>

<P><B>I thought the fish that they surfaced with </B></P>

<P><B>were all the answers they needed; </B></P>

<P><B>but now when I look at the sky they leave in their wake, </B></P>

<P><B>I'm not satisfied with the empty space. </B></P>

<P><BR>
</P>

<P><B>And I don't know about your eyes. </B></P>

<P><B>I don't think I can take them turning away. </B></P>

<P><B>I can't let them fall blue </B></P>

<P><B>anymore than I can put out the sparks </B></P>

<P><B>that plunge from the trees </B></P>

<P><B>or rake in their leaving. </B></P>

<P><B>My heart is scattered beneath you: </B></P>

<P><B>yellow, red, orange, purple, and green. </B></P>

<P><B>I don't think I'll survive this maroon understanding. </B></P>

<P><B>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Community of Writers
Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="TOTAL MENTAL SATISFACTION"></A><B>TOTAL MENTAL SATISFACTION
</B>
<P><B>Marissa Marianino, a student from Arizona </B></P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>within myself </B></P>

<P><B>I'll look deeper than imaginable </B></P>

<P><B>to build a stronger </B></P>

<P><B>sense of well-being </B></P>

<P><B>a self-esteem that no one can destroy </B></P>

<P><B>the mindset of a leader </B></P>

<P><B>determination that takes me </B></P>

<P><B>farther than I expected </B></P>

<P><B>to be so rejoiced with life </B></P>

<P><B>that it leaves me stoned and breathless </B></P>

<P><B>begging for more </B></P>

<P><B>surrounded in ecstasy </B></P>

<P><B>the strongest of love and passion </B></P>

<P><B>I'll give to myself </B></P>

<P><B>I'll acquire the flavors of life and freedom </B></P>

<P><B>to the fullest </B></P>

<P><B>and I will not stop looking </B></P>

<P><B>inside myself </B></P>

<P><B>until my mission is accomplished </B></P>

<P><B>Total mental satisfaction </B></P>

<P><B>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Community of Writers
Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><B>Click here to&nbsp;Return to the <A HREF="esv6toc.html">Volume 6
Main Menu</A></B></P>

