<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="The Queen"></A><B>The Queen </B>
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>Her black marble eyes</B></P>

<P><B>pinned me down to my spot.</B> </P>

<P><B>Dripping chins formed a runway</B> </P>

<P><B>for her toxic breath to take off</B> </P>

<P><B>into my face.</B> </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>Yellow light arced</B> </P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%><IMG SRC="confer3.jpg" HEIGHT=148 WIDTH=198></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><B>on her fatty cheeks.</B> 
<P><B>We played croquet,</B> </P>

<P><B>verdant hedges as borders.</B> </P>

<P><B>She sneered, snorted, and pranced around,</B> </P>

<P><B>each step triggering an earthquake.</B> </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>I would lose.</B> </P>

<P><B>Her foul cheating ways</B> </P>

<P><B>infuriated me the most,</B> </P>

<P><B>but as long as I didn't start her temper,</B> </P>

<P><B>I would survive.</B> </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>For I could see my blood</B> </P>

<P><B>in shiny pools on wooden planks,</B> </P>

<P><B>where my head would peel off from its neck,</B> </P>

<P><B>fanning red fountains into the air.</B> </P>

<P><B>She could get away with it!</B> </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>To play a game,</B> </P>

<P><B>where I was certain she would win,</B> </P>

<P><B>her cheating always allowed.</B> </P>

<P><B>And I had no control,</B> </P>

<P><B>for I could lose my head.</B> </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>Wonderland started to anger me,</B> </P>

<P><B>or was it the caterpillar's colored smoke,</B> </P>

<P><B>which had billowed and plumed </B></P>

<P><B>from his green puckered lips,</B> </P>

<P><B>high up on his pedestal of leaves?</B> </P>

<P><B>I could feel his black eyebrow lift</B> </P>

<P><B>to gaze at me condescendingly.</B> </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>As I awoke from the fumes,</B> </P>

<P><B>upset from the unfairness,</B> </P>

<P><B>I had done it;</B> </P>

<P><B>I had angered the Queen.</B> </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>The Jacks were ordered, </B></P>

<P><B>by her deep exploding voice,</B> </P>

<P><B>to take me away.</B> </P>

<P><B>She wanted to see me go.</B> </P>

<P><B>Her red rage flared</B> </P>

<P><B>from her nostrils. </B></P>

<P><B>Her temper was unleashed. </B></P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>The Cheshire cat watched me also</B> </P>

<P><B>through his spinning, mad eyes</B> </P>

<P><B>that looked outward</B> </P>

<P><B>over his purple striped stomach</B> </P>

<P><B>and his tail, coiled </B></P>

<P><B>around an arm of a tree.</B> </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>The last thing</B> </P>

<P><B>that filled my eyes</B> </P>

<P><B>was the Queen's</B> </P>

<P><B>malevolent grin</B> </P>

<P><B>peeling open</B> </P>

<P><B>that doughy face</B> </P>

<P><B>under those black marble eyes</B> </P>

<P><B>which watched amusingly.</B> </P>

<P><B>My head rolled away elliptically.</B> </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>-Curt Confer </B></P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="Slow Anger"></A><B>Slow Anger</B> 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>I watch you. </P>

<P>Your Anger </P>

<P>has always amused me. </P>

<P>Subtle changes </P>

<P>Head tilted a bit lower, </P>

<P>Quicker strides. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>It always takes you </P>

<P>longer to cool down from </P>

<P>Anger </P>

<P>than from </P>

<P>Joy, </P>

<P>as your </P>

<P>Hatred </P>

<P>has always been more passionate than your </P>

<P>Love. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>An insolent smile, </P>

<P>I know, </P>

<P>can only add to your anger. </P>

<P>I only want to see you </P>

<P>Break. </P>

<P>a Shout, </P>

<P>a Fist, </P>

<P>a Tear. </P>

<P>Through long years, </P>

<P>things I've never witnessed. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>All you give me </P>

<P>is an </P>

<P>Angry glance, </P>

<P>and turn </P>

<P>Away. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>by Debbi Chun </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="GRANDMA"></A><B>GRANDMA</B> 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>Her house smells </P>

<P>of a misty comfort </P>

<P>Flowered quilts lay everywhere </P>

<P>perfectly folded on matching wing chairs. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>Moving through the house, </P>

<P>the smell of potpourri mingles in the air, </P>

<P>at first nauseating. </P>

<P>Then I laugh, </P>

<P>how fitting. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>The melting apple pie </P>

<P>baking slowly in the oven </P>

<P>takes over my senses </P>

<P>as she unwraps </P>

<P>her perfectly tied apron. </P>

<P>Another day, </P>

<P>another pie. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>You move up the old </P>

<P>dark, crying stairs. </P>

<P>Each stair, another memory </P>

<P>on her wall of pictures. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>In my own bedroom </P>

<P>I'm attracted to the beautifully picked </P>

<P>and portrayed bouquet of flowers. </P>

<P>How long that took her. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>I lift the flatly ironed covers </P>

<P>from my bed </P>

<P>to see they have been folded </P>

<P>evenly into the corners. </P>

<P>I slowly drift from </P>

<P>consciousness </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>-Anna Meil </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="Turn this Bottle Upside Down"></A><B>Turn this Bottle
Upside Down</B> 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>turn this bottle upside down </P>

<P>and hear the dreams that tumble out </P>

<P>into a shimmering puddle on the dirt </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>you shall taste </P>

<P>a life of waiting </P>

<P>green and other tranquil liquids </P>

<P>waving to and fro in my mind </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>so sweep up this puddle slowly </P>

<P>and toss it under the carpet </P>

<P>there is more in the bottle still </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>shake the glass </P>

<P>as the paste of life crawls out </P>

<P>like a slug </P>

<P>leaving a long trail of slime and memories </P>

<P>all along the hatchet stone walkway </P>

<P>of my soul </P>

<P>potholes gaping and crumbling </P>

<P>from wounds never paved quite right </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>a moldable life </P>

<P>too soon marred by clumsy hands </P>

<P>a small lump of clay </P>

<P>slowly forming an old woman </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>by Sarah Haden </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="THE NIGHTTIME"></A><B>THE NIGHTTIME</B> 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>The full moon hangs low, </P>

<P>Its eerie glow the only source of light around. </P>

<P>A thick gray fog moves in across the sky, </P>

<P>Hovering over the moon like a helicopter over a criminal. </P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%><IMG SRC="rygernay.jpg" HEIGHT=222 WIDTH=188></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%>The tall pines are lined up across the forest floor 
<P>Resembling soldiers lining up and preparing for battle. </P>

<P>They stand stock still. </P>

<P>The only time they move is when </P>

<P>The gentle breeze soothingly rustles their needles. </P>

<P>A stagnant pond lies in the distance. </P>

<P>The reflection of the moonlight on the water </P>

<P>Gives it a luminous effect. </P>

<P>The twinkling stars sit suspended in the night sky, </P>

<P>Like a mobile over a baby's crib. </P>

<P>The wild animals saunter around the forest floor </P>

<P>Desperately searching for something to eat </P>

<P>Without the slightest inkling that they may be the target themselves.
</P>

<P>As the night proceeds, </P>

<P>The moon goes down and the sun comes up, </P>

<P>Its beautiful orange light </P>

<P>Just about able to peer over the horizon, </P>

<P>Like a small child over a countertop. </P>

<P>As day continues and night draws closer and closer, </P>

<P>The sun begins to descend </P>

<P>Giving the sky a purplish mien. </P>

<P>The moon comes out making its appearance known. </P>

<P>Once the sun has completed its downward journey </P>

<P>And the sky is black as coal, </P>

<P>Mother Nature continues with her nighttime cycle </P>

<P>To prepare for the dawn of the new day that awaits her. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>-Ryan Gernay </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="Moving On"></A><B>Moving On</B> 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>Some days you may find yourself being torn to pieces </P>

<P>Every rip destroys a piece of you that you worked so hard and so long
to build </P>

<P>You want to jump in and hold them back, but nothing can stop their desire
to </P>

<P>make your life miserable </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>So then you're left there all alone </P>

<P>Sobbing, begging for help, picking up the pieces </P>

<P>And then you begin to put them back together </P>

<P>Binding them stronger this time </P>

<P>Only hoping that they won't be torn down once again </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>You smile as you survive the next few blows </P>

<P>But are just waiting for another major blow to tear you down again </P>

<P>Leaving you with the pieces </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>- Michelle Rice </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="Fear"></A><B>Fear</B> 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>Fear is darkness. </P>

<P>It waits for you to let down your guard, </P>

<P>patiently. </P>

<P>It is like the dark winter air, </P>

<P>swirling around us. </P>

<P>It is like a hunter stalking his prey, </P>

<P>with persistence. </P>

<P>It is the confusion within your mind, </P>

<P>playing its evil game. </P>

<P>It is the unknown </P>

<P>that strikes fear. </P>

<P>It is what we do not understand. </P>

<P>It is what we can't comprehend. </P>

<P>It is what we run from, </P>

<P>or try to hide from. </P>

<P>It is violence waiting to destroy </P>

<P>your mind. </P>

<P>It is violence waiting to consume you </P>

<P>and your mind. </P>

<P>Fear is the unknown. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>-Peter Staples </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="HEARTBROKEN"></A>HEARTBROKEN 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>Love, where are you now? </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>I, alone and<B> heartbroken,</B> </P>

<P>need you. </P>

<P>Your fleeting embrace, the </P>

<P>touch of your lips upon mine </P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%><IMG SRC="reeds2.jpg" HEIGHT=161 WIDTH=214></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=75%>have gone and left me. 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>I, alone and <B>heartbroken</B>, </P>

<P>stand before you reflecting </P>

<P>like a pond </P>

<P>showing you what you want to </P>

<P>see instead of what you need </P>

<P>to see. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>I, alone and <B>heartbroken, </B></P>

<P>am now like the rapids being </P>

<P>smashed upon the rocks. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>I alone and<B> heartbroken</B>. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>- Scott Williamson </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=20%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="A Free Spirit"></A><B><I>A Free Spirit</I></B> 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><I>Some people say that she stands alone.</I> </P>

<P><I>That she is a free spirit.</I> </P>

<P><I>Ready, willing, and able to do whatever she wants at the spur of
the moment.</I> </P>

<P><I>Others say that she is out of control, or maybe that she has a bad
reputation for voicing her opinion.</I> </P>

<P><I>Yet this does not phase her. </I></P>

<P><I>She blows it right off.</I> </P>

<P><I>She does not care about what others think is right and what is wrong.
</I></P>

<P><I>She only cares about her thoughts and what she thinks is right.</I>
</P>

<P><I>She has her own mind and her own values.</I> </P>

<P><I>One of her values is that she does not judge a person by what they
look like, but on their personality.</I> </P>

<P><I>Reputation means little to her. </I></P>

<P><I>There are some people who make fun of her clothes, her hair, and
her friends. </I></P>

<P><I>When they laugh she merely just shrugs it off, and figures that it
is just jealousy or low self-esteem.</I> </P>

<P><I>She is as free as a bird who can just soar all day long. </I></P>

<P><I>With her dreams she reaches for the stars </I></P>

<P><I>and will not give up until she grabs them.</I> </P>

<P><I>But there are some who are afraid to reach, afraid to dream, afraid
to be.</I> </P>

<P><I>Those who are will never live life to its fullest, and never be the
dream.</I> </P>

<P><I>by Marianna Sparata</I> </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="A Soft Empty Black to Call my Own"></A><B>A Soft
Empty Black to Call my Own</B> 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>I lie awake in a sea of black. </P>

<P>I've been staring at the ceiling </P>

<P>For over an hour, tossing from side to side, </P>

<P>Wondering when I will drift, but I don't. </P>

<P>Something in my mind won't let me. </P>

<P>Too many covers, too much light. </P>

<P>I don't know what it is, but it is there. </P>

<P>I keep looking at the red numbers, slowly changing. </P>

<P>If I fall asleep now, I get seven hours of sleep. </P>

<P>Now it is six and a half; now it is six. </P>

<P>The numbers get smaller and smaller. </P>

<P>And still, I twist and turn </P>

<P>In this soft empty blackness </P>

<P>That I spend my every night escaping </P>

<P>From the days that I spend suffocating. </P>

<P>-Ryan Miller </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%><A NAME="Twin Pools"></A><B>Twin Pools</B> 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>Twin pools of deepest brown </P>

<P>Gaze down upon her face, </P>

<P>Upon the skin like cream, </P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%><IMG SRC="brlittel.jpg" HEIGHT=139 WIDTH=148></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%>Framed by hair of midnight. 
<P>His face betrays nothing of what he feels, </P>

<P>But his eyes cannot shadow </P>

<P>What is in his heart. </P>

<P>He sighs softly, </P>

<P>Not knowing what she thinks of him. </P>

<P>He longs to take her in his arms </P>

<P>And carry her away from this harsh reality </P>

<P>To a place where she cannot be hurt any more. </P>

<P>But, alas, his heart is not strong, </P>

<P>And forces block him at all turns. </P>

<P>So he hugs her, </P>

<P>Love shining through his eyes </P>

<P>As a single tear traces his cheek. </P>

<P>-Bryan Littel </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="cy_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=70%><A NAME="Spring"></A><B>Spring</B> 
<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>Warm breeze breathing down my neck, </P>

<P>Playing with my hair. </P>

<P>The air gently whispers in my ear. </P>

<P>Cool grass between my toes, </P>

<P>Soft dew tickling my feet, </P>

<P>Moistened ground keeps me chilled. </P>
</TD>

<TD width=25%><IMG SRC="berry.jpg" HEIGHT=155 WIDTH=122></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=60%>The rays beat on my shoulders, 
<P>Steam rising off my back, </P>

<P>My skin is tanned by the sun. </P>

<P>My body feels alive and free, </P>

<P>Running wild </P>

<P>On a beautiful spring day. </P>

<P>-Nicole Baker </P>

<P><IMG SRC="whball.gif" HEIGHT=18 WIDTH=18><B>Return to<A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">
Poetry Main Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=35%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

