<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="Retrospect"></A><B>Retrospect</B> 
<P>Sordid storm chants bitterly (k) </P>

<P>Delirious vision shines on the winter shadow (d) </P>

<P>Raw sea spray moans a symphony (k) </P>

<P>Summer garden whispers sweetly to the screaming boy (d) </P>

<P>White mist beneath a red moon (k) </P>

<P>Tiny pictures of Spring blow in the wind (d) </P>

<P>Bitter sweet power manipulates life (k) </P>

<P>Dream crushed like a delicate summer rose (d) </P>

<P>Milk runs from the black sky (k) </P>

<P>Love incubates in a windy void (k) </P>

<P>Frantic life rusts languidly (kd) </P>

<P>After it is gone and behind me (kd) </P>

<P><BR>
</P>

<P>Katie Lynch (k) &amp; Dan DeLorenzo (d) </P>

<P>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Magnetic, Linked, and Form
Poetry Menu</A></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="WINTER'S CALM TEMPEST"></A><B>WINTER'S CALM TEMPEST</B>

<P>In the spicy air an old house sways with the wind, ice sheets on the
roof. </P>

<P>Water stands solid, building and growing on the houses, encasing those
who dwell inside. </P>

<P>Snow sits quietly while the wind blows harshly, icicles threaten the
delicate floor. </P>

<P>Piercing this floor, single strands of occasional green push through
the ice and snow. </P>

<P>A single barren tree pushes its branches outward, up towards the desolate
sky. </P>

<P>The living arms push higher toward the islands of vaporous clouds, looking
for a place to escape the harsh sea of blue. </P>

<P>-Erin Schneidermann &amp; Rob Wavra .</P>

<P>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Magnetic, Linked, and Form
Poetry Menu</A></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=40%><IMG SRC="jbasedow.jpg" HEIGHT=219 WIDTH=206></TD>

<TD WIDTH=55%><A NAME="FOREST WHISPERS"></A><B>FOREST WHISPERS</B> 
<P>smooth shadows will stop dreams like iron </P>

<P>whisper your vision beneath diamond forests </P>

<P>goddess please </P>

<P>only sing of frantic whispers </P>

<P>that soar over the rain </P>

<P>fly over the mist above </P>

<P>winter as summer's white gown </P>

<P>shadow beauty is bitter blood </P>

<P>forest whispers falling through like a knife </P>

<P>-Jarrett Basedow </P>

<P>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Magnetic, Linked, and Form
Poetry Menu</A></P>
</TD>

<TD width=25%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="VISIONS"></A><B>VISIONS</B> 
<P>A thousand visions </P>

<P>like after frantic, </P>

<P>delicate moments, </P>

<P>essentially delirious, </P>

<P>ripped raw, </P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%><IMG SRC="cchun.jpg" HEIGHT=156 WIDTH=191> </TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%>drunken power flooding - 
<P>mad as love; </P>

<P>smooth, easy, bitter </P>

<P>as rain, </P>

<P>as storm, </P>

<P>as need, </P>

<P>as love... </P>

<P>symphonies around me of </P>

<P>hair and legs and sweat and </P>

<P>sleep, </P>

<P>beautiful - </P>

<P>always </P>

<P>shadows - </P>

<P>always, </P>

<P>falling, singing, aching </P>

<P>rose petals, </P>

<P>the music of water, </P>

<P>fast misty pictures </P>

<P>the whispered language of skin: </P>

<P>always true - </P>

<P>I the watcher. </P>

<P>-Carolyn Chun </P>

<P>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Magnetic, Linked, and Form
Poetry Menu</A></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="Remember"></A><B>Remember</B> 
<P>My elderly face, with old fingers, </P>

<P>looked up at the strange, old door. </P>

<P>Its white cracked paint stood still and quiet, </P>

<P>as it has since I was four. <BR>
<BR>
</P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%><IMG SRC="eschneid.jpg" HEIGHT=101 WIDTH=214></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%>I looked at the door and it looked at me, 
<P>withered and slightly cold, </P>

<P>I took it in and held my breath. </P>

<P>and remembered all the stories it told. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>A step inside and I felt a chill. </P>

<P>rush through my body with fright. </P>

<P>A cobweb stood above my head. </P>

<P>a spider eating to its heart's delight. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>I brushed it away and stood very still </P>

<P>so as not to make a sound. </P>

<P>One step at a time, I made my way through, </P>

<P>staying low and close to the ground. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>The potent smell of gases circling the air </P>

<P>rang in my head, </P>

<P>but I stayed strong and held my breath, </P>

<P>with small steps and with great care. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>The concrete walls stood tall and hard; </P>

<P>the wood floors cold and bleak. </P>

<P>my head felt strange and very light, </P>

<P>and I could hardly speak. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>I remembered the horrors that happened here, </P>

<P>the pained and agonized faces. </P>

<P>the lines, the smell, the work and trouble </P>

<P>to keep us in our places. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>I felt a pain run in my mind, </P>

<P>of hard times every day. </P>

<P>I can't forgive for what occured; </P>

<P>I can only hope and pray. </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>-Erin Schneiderman </P>

<P>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Magnetic, Linked, and Form
Poetry Menu</A></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="MORE TEA"></A><B><I>MORE TEA</I></B> 
<P>&quot;More tea?&quot; she asked, </P>

<P>offering him a pink plastic cup. </P>

<P>He growled his pleasure, </P>

<P>and she smiled, tugging half-heartedly </P>

<P>at the ribbon wound into her golden curls. </P>

<P>He reaches out but falls short. </P>

<P>He realizes his arm is stuffed, and </P>

<P>Wait, he can't move. </P>

<P>The teacup falls to the marble floor </P>

<P>and shatters into a million pieces, </P>

<P>cutting her bare hands and turning her pristine white dress </P>

<P>into horrid shades of red and pink </P>

<P>tye-dyed in her own blood. </P>

<P>She screamed her shattering pain </P>

<P>as Mr. Bear looked on helplessly </P>

<P>with his black button eye, </P>

<P>unable to reach, lifeless. </P>

<P>-Jarrett Basedow and Monica Stahl </P>

<P>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Magnetic, Linked, and Form
Poetry Menu</A></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="DARKNESS"></A><B>DARKNESS</B> 
<P>The seasons have changed </P>

<P>So many times, but this year </P>

<P>The dark came earlier </P>

<P>Encompassing </P>

<P>It swallows my soul </P>

<P>Its hold firm on my consciousness </P>

<P>I disappear into the night </P>

<P>Engulfed by the lack of light </P>

<P>The darkness surrounds me </P>

<P>and I begin to fall </P>

<P>Gravity pulls me down </P>

<P>Faster </P>

<P>Faster </P>

<P>I feel myself hitting the ground </P>

<P>Darkness </P>

<P>-Anita Kulkarni and Dan DeLorenzo</P>

<P>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Magnetic, Linked, and Form
Poetry Menu</A></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="Sonnet"></A><B>Sonnet</B> 
<P>You were always there for me. </P>

<P>Oh, I hope the memories do not fade. </P>

<P>Sitting under the old apple tree. </P>

<P>On those long summer days talking in the shade. </P>

<P>Wishing on that one shooting star. </P>

<P>Looking at the gold sparks in your eyes. </P>

<P>Hoping that you would not go too far. </P>

<P>I wish that I could be that wise. </P>

<P>You will not leave without putting up a fight, </P>

<P>And I wish we did not have to part. </P>

<P>All those other times you seemed to be full of delight. </P>

<P>You will always be in my heart. </P>

<P>Someday I will understand why you had to go, </P>

<P>But for now I do not know. </P>

<P>-Robyn Cromen </P>

<P>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Magnetic, Linked, and Form
Poetry Menu</A></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="WISH"></A><B>WISH</B> 
<P>The last sun rays play on the clouds </P>

<P>As they dance through the air; </P>

<P>Bathing the sky in such radiant ways </P>

<P>The eyes can't help but stare. </P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%><IMG SRC="sunset2.jpg" HEIGHT=111 WIDTH=239></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%>The sun slowly comes down, 
<P>Down from its throne in the sky. </P>

<P>It slowly settles over the hills </P>

<P>As in it's bed beneath it lies. </P>

<P>The colors deepen. </P>

<P>The sun drifts off to sleep. </P>

<P>The glamour all gone </P>

<P>The memories we keep. </P>

<P>The Cheshire Cat grins, </P>

<P>Showing his crescent shaped teeth. </P>

<P>One by one, </P>

<P>Diamond-like stars begin to peep. </P>

<P>Close your eyes; </P>

<P>Look into your heart. </P>

<P>Look where there are no lies, </P>

<P>And make a wish for the better part. </P>

<P>So many wishes I've made. </P>

<P>They may not all come true. </P>

<P>But one wish I know lives on, </P>

<P>The day I met you. </P>

<P>-April Stone</P>

<P>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Magnetic, Linked, and Form
Poetry Menu</A></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="rd_bar.gif" HEIGHT=11 WIDTH=640></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=30%><A NAME="HAIKU"></A><B>HAIKU</B> 
<P>Tracks in the white dust </P>

<P>snow angels are left behind </P>

<P>the warm sun blazes </P>

<P>-by Jarrett Basedow</P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>Darkness envelopes </P>

<P>Moisture collects into drops </P>

<P>Murky skies dissolve </P>

<P>-by Alison Quairoli </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="Sun falls"></A>Sun falls </P>

<P>wandering bird tries to catch </P>

<P>the last glimpse of light </P>

<P>-by Faith Wilson </P>
</TD>

<TD width=20%></TD>

<TD width=40%><BR>
Ice engulfs the house 
<P>An open perfume bottle </P>

<P>Engraved in concrete </P>

<P>-by Ryan Gernay </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P>Cloud coming close </P>

<P>Offers fear as </P>

<P>lightning makes its mark </P>

<P>-by Faith Wilson </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><A NAME="Blackness is torn"></A>Blackness is torn </P>

<P>bright light rips through sky </P>

<P>Then thunder - it's gone </P>

<P>-by Faith Wilson </P>
</TD>

<TD width=5%></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

