<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="SHE"></A><B>SHE </B>
<P><B>by Nitasha Bansal</B> </P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<P><B>walking down the hall,</B> </P>

<P><B>there SHE is</B> </P>

<P><B>always</B> </P>

<P><B>surrounded by friends.</B> </P>

<P><B>Friends?</B> </P>

<P><B>no, not really</B> </P>

<P><B>SHE hurts them,</B> </P>

<P><B>hurts them always</B> </P>

<P><B>again and again</B> </P>

<P><B>Insecurity?</B> </P>

<P><B>yes, definitely</B> </P>

<P><B>Why do they bother?</B> </P>

<P><B>is SHE right?</B> </P>

<P><B>Wrong?</B> </P>

<P><B>Does SHE understand?</B> </P>

<P><B>Does SHE?</B> </P>

<P><B>DOES SHE?</B> </P>

<P><B>Tell me!</B> </P>

<P><B>Why?</B> </P>

<P><B>Too fickle</B> </P>

<P><B>Too different, yet . . .</B> </P>

<P><B>Too much alike</B> </P>

<P><B>Why do I bother?</B> </P>

<P><B>My mind, her mind</B> </P>

<P><B>To hurt,</B> </P>

<P><B>WHY?!</B> </P>

<P><B>Could she <I>possibly</I> understand?</B> </P>

<P><B>No (ha, ha)</B> </P>

<P><B>how could SHE?</B> </P>

<P><B>Too seemingly perfect. </B></P>

<P><B>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Young Writers Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="barfrac1.gif" HEIGHT=17 WIDTH=555></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=30%><IMG SRC="sunset.jpg" HEIGHT=226 WIDTH=160></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="Skyline"></A><B>Skyline </B>
<P><B>by Jonathan Miller</B> </P>

<P><B>A WHITE mural above,</B> </P>

<P><B>Painted with specks of BLUE</B> </P>

<P><B>Cotton balls in the sky grow</B> </P>

<P><B>To enormous beasts.</B> </P>

<P><B>The same mural is now BLUE</B> </P>

<P><B>With specks of WHITE</B> </P>

<P><B>A yellow ball of light</B> </P>

<P><B>Fills the hills with warmth.</B> </P>

<P><B>Soon it fades</B> </P>

<P><B>The mural now screams</B> </P>

<P><B>Bright lines of PINK and ORANGE</B> </P>

<P><B>Fill the horizon.</B> </P>

<P><B>In time it fades to BLACK</B> </P>

<P><B>The show seems to have ended</B> </P>

<P><B>The sky fills with a thousand lights</B> </P>

<P><B>The show has only begun.</B> </P>

<P><B>BLACK fades back to PINK</B> </P>

<P><B>Then WHITE</B> </P>

<P><B>Then BLUE</B> </P>

<P><B>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Young Writers Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="barfrac1.gif" HEIGHT=17 WIDTH=555></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="The show continues on. . . . . .Mom, I Want to be"></A><B>Mom,
I Want to be a Squirrel</B> 
<P><B>by Ryan Miller</B> </P>

<P><B>Ryan is a senior here at HCRHS, exploring </B></P>

<P><B>his creativity by writing for young children.</B> </P>

<P><B>&quot;Mom, I want to be a squirrel,&quot;</B> </P>

<P><B>the boy said one bright sunny day,</B> </P>

<P><B>&quot;And run around in the woods</B> </P>

<P><B>Eating nuts and berries and seeds and stuff.&quot;</B> </P>

<P><B>&quot;I don't think that's possible,&quot; his mother said,</B> </P>

<P><B>&quot;for squirrels live in the woods and are small.</B> </P>

<P><B>You live in a house and are big.&quot;</B> </P>

<P><B>And with that she went back to her book.</B> </P>

<P><B>The boy stood puzzled for a moment</B> </P>

<P><B>But then got the most brilliant idea</B> </P>

<P><B>&quot;How about I get your grey fur coat</B> </P>

<P><B>And put a dusting brush on my butt?&quot;</B> </P>

<P><B>&quot;You'd still be a boy though,&quot; the mother said,</B> </P>

<P><B>&quot;Only you'd be running around in a big fur coat</B> </P>

<P><B>Eating nuts and berries and seeds and stuff in a tree.&quot;</B>
</P>

<P><B>And with that the mother proudly thought she had won.</B> </P>

<P><B>The boy was only temporarily discouraged by that,</B> </P>

<P><B>But then ran into the house and returned with a box on his back.</B>
</P>

<P><B>&quot;I'd settle to be a turtle down by the creek,&quot; the boy
said.</B> </P>

<P><B>And it went on and on and on like that all day.</B> </P>

<P><B>So the moral of this story is for the kids:</B> </P>

<P><B>&quot;Never give up on becoming what you want</B> </P>

<P><B>And eventually your parents will break down</B> </P>

<P><B>And buy you the transmorgrifier you wanted for Christmas.&quot;</B>
</P>

<P><B>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Young Writers Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="barfrac1.gif" HEIGHT=17 WIDTH=555></P>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD width=5%></TD>

<TD width=65%><A NAME="Untitled"></A><B>Untitled</B> 
<P><B>by Danica Rue</B> </P>

<P><B>The lightning crashes</B> </P>

<P><B>and breaks the silence we never used to have.</B> </P>

<P><B>The loss of words is almost unbearable</B> </P>

<P><B>yet it doesn't phase her at all.</B> </P>

<P><B>She doesn't remember the fun times we used to have</B> </P>

<P><B>because she has all her new friends</B> </P>

<P><B>We made the promise</B> </P>

<P><B>she never kept</B> </P>

<P><B>to</B> <B>be friends till death.</B> </P>

<P><B>Return to <A HREF="#Electric Soup Community">Young Writers Menu</A></B></P>
</TD>

<TD width=30%></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><B>Click here to&nbsp;Return to the <A HREF="esv6toc.html">Volume 6
Main Menu</A></B></P>

