<b><h2><center>Changing Celcius to Fahrenheit</center></h2></b>

<h3>C = F - 32/1.8</h3>

OR

<h3>C = 5/9(F-32)</h3>

Note: C stands for Celcius degrees and F stands for Fahrenheit degrees.<br>

<a href="basics.html"><h5>Go Back to the Basics of the Metric System</h5></a>
<a href="fahren.html"><h5>Go to 
Converting Fahrenheit to Celcius</h5></a>



