<b><h2><center>Changing Fahrenheit to Celcius</center></h2></b>

<h3>F = (C x 1.8) + 32</h3>

OR

<h3>F = 5/9C + 32</h3>

Note: C stands for Celcius degrees and F stands for Fahrenheit degrees.

