<b><h1><center>Multiples of Ten</center></h1></b>
Since the Metric System is based on multiples of 10, it is easy to convert a unit to larger or smaller units just by moving the decimal point.  For instance, to convert 1 meter to centimeters, all you have to do is mulitply by 100 (since one centimeter is 1/100 of a meter) to find that 1 meter = 100 centimeters.  There is no difficult arithmetic involved.<br>


<a href="basics.html"><h5>Go Back to the Basics of the Metric System</a><br>
