<b><h2><center>Mass</center></h2></b><br>

The mass of something is a measurement of the amoun of matter it contains.  Thus, the amount of matter an object contains is the same despite the force gravity exerts upon iit.  Because of this, scientists always use mass to weigh an object; no matter where they are, the mass, the amount of matter, is the same. 



