<b><h2><center>Density</center></h2></b>

This measures how tightly packed the atoms are in an object.  We often compare the density of a liqued to that of water.  If you've ever looked at oil and vinegar in a jar, you've noticed that the oil floats on top.  Thus, oil is less dense than both vinegar and water.  Since the vinegar sinks, it is more dense than oil and of equal or more density than water.




