<b><h2><center>Heat</center></h2></b>

This is defined as the vibration of molecules.  Heat passes from molecule to molecule through vibration (except in RADIATION).  An object feels hot or cold depending upon how rapidly its molecules are moving.  When the molecules of an object vibrate quickly, the temperature of an object rises.

