<h2 align=center><b>Cold</b></h2>

<p><img src="gif/freezing.gif" height=200 width=200 align=right>Cold does
not exist. Instead, it is the absence of heat. Since everything in the
universe has molecules (which are always vibrating), everything has heat,
it is just the amount (how quickly the molecules are vibrating) that differ.
<hr></p>

<h5><a href="hot.html">Go to Heat</a></h5>
