<b><h2><center>Conductors and Insulators</center></h2></b>

<center><u><IMG SRC="gif/smile.gif"><a href="transfer.html"><h5>Go Back to Heat Transfer
</h5></a></u></center><hr>

<b><img align= top src="gif/redcube.gif" ALT="* ">   <a href="#conductor"<h3>Conductors</h3></a>  
	<UL>
	<LI><a href="#metal"><b>
Example:  Metals</a><br></UL>
	<b><img align= top src="gif/redcube.gif" ALT="* ">   <a href="#insulators">Insulators</a><br> 
<UL><LI><a href="#example"><b><h4>Example:  Blankets</h4></a><br></UL><hr><br><br><br>



<a name="conductor"></a><u><h2>Conductors</h2></u>

These are materials that transfer heat.<br>

<a href="conins.html"><h5>Go to 
Top of Conductors and Insulators</h5></a><br>
<a href="#metal"><h5>Go to Example:  Metals</h5></a><hr><br>



<a name="metal"></a><u><h3>Example: Metals</h3></u>

Metals allows the heat of a flame of a stove to travel through it so you are able to cook your food.<br>


<a href="conins.html"><h5>Go to 
Top of Conductors and Insulators</h5></a>
<a href="#conductor"><h5>Go Back to Conductors</h5></a>
<a href="#insulators"><h5>Go to Insulators</h5></a><hr><br>


<a name="insulators"></a><u><h2>Insulators</h2></u>

These are materials that do not transfer heat.  A wooden handle on a spoon stops the flow of heat so that your hand won't be burned.  Gasses are also poor conductors of heat.  If you place you hand near a hot iron, you will not be burned.  Almost any material with air spaces in it is a good insulator.<br>

<a href="conins.html"><h5>Go to 
Top of Conductors and Insulators</h5></a>
<a href="#example"><h5>Go to Example:  Blankets</h5></a><hr>

<a name="example"></a><u><h3>Example:  Blankets</h3></u>

Ever wonder how blankets keep you warm on a cold winter's evening? <br> 

Actually, they do not keep you warm; in fact, your body heat keeps them warm.  Since they are insulators (they contain many air holes), they keep your body heat from escaping into the air of the room.


<a href="conins.html"><h5>Go to 
Top of Conductors and Insulators</h5></a>
<a href="#insulators"><h5>Go Back to Insulators</h5></a>




