<h2><b><center>Oxygen</center></b></h2>
<center><u><IMG SRC="Gif/Smile.gif"><a href="bpoint.html"><h5>Go Back the Boiling Point</h5></a></u></center><hr>

<h4><center>What is the effect of oxygen have on the boiling point of water?</center><br></h4>

Without oxygen, it will take a beaker longer to boil.  However, both beakers (with and without oxygen) will boil at the same temperature.  Beaker A, the one without oxygen, took 14 minutes to reach its boiling point of 100 degrees Celcius.  Beaker B, the one with the oxygen, took just 8 minutes and 30 seconds to reach the same boiling point, 100 degrees Celcius.


