<h1><u><center>Dikes</center></u></h1>

<center><u><IMG SRC="gif/smile.gif"><a href="intrude.html"><h5>Go Back to Intrusive Vulcanism</h5></a></u></center><hr>

These occur when the intrudeing magma dries vertically across layers of horizontal rock.  They range from a few inches thick to several hundred feet thick.  It also may extend many miles below the earth's surface.<br>
Sometimes, because the dikes are composed of igneous rock, they are able to withstand erosion, while the rock neighboring them (sedimetary rock) erodes.  There are some huge exposed dikes extending from the Spanish Peaks in Colorado. <br>


