<h1><u><center>Sills</center></u></h1>

<center><u><IMG SRC="gif/smile.gif"><a href="intrude.html"><h5>Go Back to Intrusive Vulcanism</h5></a></u></center><hr>

These occur when the intruding magma solidifies between horizontal layers of rock.  They form parallel to other layers and may be several hundred feet or several hundred miles long.<br>
These, too, may also erode to the surface after time (usually through a river washing over its surface).  The Palisades of the Hudson River in New York and New Jersey are part of a great sill.
<br>

<a href="stock.html">To Stocks</a><br> 
<a href="bath.html">To Batholiths</a><br> 
<a href="lacc.html">To Laccoliths</a><br>
