<h1><u><center>Stocks</center></u></h1>

<center><u><IMG SRC="gif/smile.gif"><br><a href="intrude.html">Go Back to Intrusive Vulcanism</a></u></center><hr>

These are almost identical to <a href="bath.html">batholiths</a> except for size.  A stock is usually less than 40 square miles in area.  When the other rock is eroded away, a stock may look like a volcanic neck, the last part of a volcano to be exposed due to the forces of erosion.
<br>


