<h1><u><center>The Ring of Fire</center></u></h1>

<center><u><IMG SRC="gif/smile.gif"><a href="ptech.html"><h5>Go Back to Plate Tectonics</a></h5></a></u></center><hr>

Because the edge of the Pacific Basin is outline in <a href="subduct.html">subduction zones </a> and <a href="diverge.html">divergent boundaries</a>, it is extremely susceptible to volcanoes.  Indeed, this 30,000 mile long ring contains about 70% of the world's more than 500 historically active volcanoes.<br>

