<h1><u><center>Seismic Waves</center></u></h1>

<center><u><IMG SRC="gif/smile.gif"><a href="earthgen.html"><h5>Go Back to General Information on Earthquakes</h5></a></u></center><hr>

Seismic waves, vibrations of an earthquake, help define layers of the earth.  You can tell what kind of material is down there by the time it takes a certain point.  It takes longer for the waves to go through a liquid than it does to go through a solid.  This was how we discovered that the mantle and outer core were liquid while the crust and inner core were solid.  Contrary to popular belief, nobody ever dug a hole deep enough to figure it out that way.  (No, you can't dig to China, either.)<br>

Remember; Seismic Waves are earthquake waves, seismologists measure them, and seismologists study them.<br>

<a href="eandv.html">To Top of Seismic Waves</a><br>
<a href="earthgen.html">To General Information on Earthquakes</a><br>
<a href="richter.html">Continue Reading about the Richter Scale</a>
