<h1><u><center>Faulty Property?</center></u></h1>

<center><u><IMG SRC="gif/smile.gif"><a href="earthgen.html"><h5>Go Back to General Information on Earthquakes</h5></a></u></center><hr>

Because no one else would buy property on faults (plus, it was a lot cheaper), the city of San Francisco did.  Consequently, fire stations, schools, and hospitals are all on the San Andreas Fault.  Other towns have done the same thing; our town of Flemington has.  On the Flemington Fault, there is the library, the park, the police/fire station, and some schools. <br><br>

<h4>What is everyone to do if there's an earthquake?</h4>

<a href="property.html">Go to Top of Faulty Property</a><br>
<a href="earthgen.html">Go Back to General Information on Earthquakes</a><br>
