<h1><u><center>Tsunamis</center></u></h1>

<center><u><IMG SRC="gif/smile.gif"><a href="earthgen.html"><h5>Go Back to General Information on Earthquakes</h5></a></u></center><hr>

Tsunamis are giant title waves caused by earthquakes.  Everyone always hears about destruction on land due to earthquakes, but what about the oceans?  Water also needs a place to vent its fury, so trunamis are the result.  Once, in Alaska in 1964, an 18 foot wall of water crashed to the shore.<br>
<a href="tsunam.html">Go to Top of Tsunamis</a><br>
<a href="earthgen.html">Go Back to General Information on Earthquakes</a>
