<center><h2><u><b>Paleontology Multimedia Project</b></u></h2></center>

<h4>Students Paleontology Project must teach the following concepts:
<UL>
A.  What is a fossil?<br>
B.  How are fossils formed?<br>
C.  What types of fossils will we collect?<br>
D.  Where will we go to collect fossils?  Why? (Why not Flemington?)<br>
E.  What were the creatures like when they were alive?  Are there any similar life forms on earth today?<br>
F.  During what Geologic Period did "our" fossils creature live?<br>
G.  What are the classes of fossils found on our trip? (Define class)<br>
H.  In what type/class of rocks are "our" fossils found?<br>
</UL></h4>

<h3><u>Outline of Project</u></h3>

<h4>Students and their lab partners have to submit a detailed outline <i>before</i> they start their computer
project.  (Has to be initialed by their teacher)</h4>

<h3><u>Things to Remember</u></h3>

<h4>Remember your directory is MMSBOOK/646<br>
Return to Main Menu button has to be on every page.<br>
How much text on each page???<br>
Full page graphics???<br>
Sound???(If have sound, must go with their program)<br>
Credits (Give credit to books used, where they got their information, and to students who did project)</h4>

