<center><h2><u><b>Saylorsburg Fossil Site</b></u></h2></center>
<h4>
Students will have to locate this stop on their New Jersey Map.<br><br>

Students also have to answer question in their booklet.  Some examples of these question are:<br><br>

<OL>
A.  What class of rock is found here (Igneous, Sedimentary, Metamorphic)?
<h5>Answer:  Sedimentary</h5>
B.  What must have covered this area at one time?  How do you know?
<h5>Answer:  Water or and ocean must have covered this area at one time.  We know this because 
all the fossils found here are marine.</h5>
</OL>
Students have to collect as many different kinds of fossils that they can.  In order to pass
the fossils unit students have to collect five of the eight classes.  Back at school students have
to clean and identify the fossils they collect.  They will also be graded on their collections.</h4>

