<A HREF="warford3.html"><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="gif/warford2.gif"></A>
<BR>
</center>

Here, the shale and the argillite seem to "interfinger" indicating that we are near a contact
zone between the two rock types.  In this stream bed there is also evidence of pre-historic
weather conditions.  (click on picture to continue)
</B>
</HTML>
