<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>holland1</TITLE></HEAD>
<B>
<img align=top src="gif/blueball.gif">
<A border=4 HREF="falltrip.html">Return to Opening Page</A><BR>
<center>
<A HREF="holland2.html"><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="gif/holland1.gif"></A>
<BR>
</center>

Continuing our northward journey, the road widens considerably and passes the
small village church at Holland Township.  This marks the site of a large fault, known 
as the Triassiac Border Fault.  It is considered the boundary between the newer Triassic sediments 
and the much older Precambrian basement rock known as Losee Gneiss.  (click on picture to continue)
</B>
</HTML>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT24-B40-122</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA003-000024-B012-92</DOCOLDNO>
