<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>holland2</TITLE></HEAD>
<B>
<img align=top src="gif/blueball.gif">
<A border=4 HREF="falltrip.html">Return to Opening Page</A><BR>
<center>
<A HREF="holland3.html"><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="gif/holland2.gif"></A>
<BR>
</center>

About one quarter mile past the church, you can collect this ancient rock which 
underlays much of Hunterdon County.  This rock was formed deep below the surface
under extremes of heat and pressure - resulting in the crystallized metamorphic Gneiss. (click on picture to continue)
</B>
</HTML>
</DOC>
