<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>holland3</TITLE></HEAD>
<B>
<img align=top src="gif/blueball.gif">
<A border=4 HREF="falltrip.html">Return to Opening Page</A><BR>
<img align=top src="gif/blueball.gif">
<A border=4 HREF="geo_over.html">Return to Geology Menu</A><BR>
During this short trip, we visited the 4 major sedimentary rocks known as the
Newark Series (which actually extend from New England to the Appalachians).  In addition,
we also visited the igneous intrusion at Byram and the much older precambrian Gneiss.

<center>
