<HEAD>
<TITLE>WIC Western Internationl Communications Ltd.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/wic.gif" WIDTH=532 HEIGHT=107 BORDER=0>
</CENTER> 

<P>
<B>WIC Western International Communications Ltd.</B> is an integrated Canadian communications, broadcast and
entertainment company with its head office in Vancouver, British Columbia.  <B>WIC</B> is the only Canadian broadcasting
company operating in television, pay television, radio and satellite network services.  <B>WIC</B> owns eight television and
eleven radio stations across Canada and is a shareholder in the CTV Television Network.  
<P>
Through Westcom Entertainment Group Ltd., <B>WIC</B> is involved in the development and production of Canadian
films and television programs.  <B>WIC</B> operates two radio networks and is involved in national advertising sales - in
television through the full ownership of Western Broadcast Sales Ltd., and in radio through a 50 per cent interest in Canadian
Broadcast Sales.
<P>
<B>WIC</B> is the pay television licensee in Western Canada for Superchannel and Home Theatre, a pay-per-view service.
<B>WIC</B> also owns 50 per cent of the Family Channel.  As well, <B>WIC</B> owns 52.6 per cent of Canadian Satellite 
Communications Inc. (Cancom).  <B>WIC</B> has also acquired an option for the exclusive Canadian rights to an
innovative cellular distribution technology for television, telephone, radio and data signals called CellularVision.


<HR>

<H3><CENTER><A HREF="wictv.htm">Broadcast &amp; Pay Television Operations</A></CENTER>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="wicradio.htm">Radio Operations</A></CENTER> 
<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="westcom.htm">Westcom Entertainment Group</A>
</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="cancom.htm">CANCOM</A> </CENTER>
