<HEAD>

<TITLE>CANCOM</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/cancom.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>


<P>
Cancom Network Operations manages the television signals for its
cable and Direct-To-Home satellite services, plus a number of
radio signals, from a Master Control Centre (MCC) in Mississauga,
Ontario. The centre is located in a building with an excellent
line of sight to satellites and freedom from microwave interferences.
<BR>
In May 1994, both WIC and Cancom joined in the formation of an
industry-wide consortium to establish a Direct-To-Home marketing
company. More than 100 digital channels of satellite programming
services will be offered to subscribers across Canada who will
receive the signals via a two-foot-wide satellite receiving dish.
The service is expected to be operational by the fall of 1995.
<HR>

<H2>Management</H2>

<UL>
<LI>Alain Gourd - President and C.E.O.
<LI>Claude Lewis - Executive Vice-President
<LI>Colley Clarke - Vice-President, Finance, Administration and
Human Resources
<LI>Lawrence Corke - Vice-President &amp; General Manager, Cable
Market Services
<LI>Paul Racine - Vice-President, Regulatory, Corporate and
Native Affairs
<LI>Tom Pirner - Vice-President, Cancom
Business Networks
<LI>Larry Steinman - Vice-President, Cancom Business Television
<LI>John Underhill - Vice-President, Network Operations
<LI>Jonathan B. Festinger - Secretary and General Counsel
</UL>
