<HEAD>
<TITLE>"JAG" premieres January 3, 1997 on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>


<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>December 2, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;JAG&quot;</H1>
<H2>premieres January 3, 1997 on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>


<P>
<I><B>JAG</B></I>, the action drama about an elite staff of Naval
officers who travel the world to investigate and prosecute military
crimes, premieres <U>Friday, January 3, 1997 (9:00 - 10:00 p.m.)</U>,
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>. <BR>

<P>
The consistently popular series, which debuted in the fall of
1995, stars <B>David James Elliott, Catherine Bell, Patrick Labyorteaux
</B>and<B> John M. Jackson</B>. <BR>

<P>
<I><B>JAG</B></I>, military jargon for Judge Advocate General's
corps, centres on a group of Naval officers whose training as
investigators and lawyers brings them face-to-face with such military
crimes as murder, treason, espionage and terrorism.<BR>

<P>
Donald Bellisario (<I>Quantum Leap, Magnum P.I.</I>) is the executive
producer.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>JAG </B></I>premieres <U>Friday, January 3, 1997, at 9:00
p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>.<BR>


<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
