<HEAD>

<TITLE>"The OUAA University Game of the Week" on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../images/prog_day.gif" ALT="Daytime Programming on CHCH-TV" WIDTH=526 HEIGHT=87 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>

<H1><CENTER>The University Game of the Week</CENTER></H1>

<P>
The <I><B>University Game of the Week</B></I> kicks
off another season of gridiron action starting Saturday, September
7, 1996 (2:00 -5:00 p.m.), on CHCH-TV as the Laurier Golden Hawks
take on the Western Mustangs. 
<P>
Joining the returning football commentating team
of Paul Hendrick and sideline analyst Ken Welch is 10 year CFL
veteran Neil Lumsden, the Hamilton Tiger-Cats' current General
Manager and Director of Business Operations.
<P>
When the basketball season commences in January 1997,
Paul Hendrick and former NBA player with the Washington Bullets,
Brian Heaney, will cover the college sports zone.
<P>
Popular features such as &quot;Player Profile,&quot;
&quot;Hits of the Week,&quot; &quot;Fan of the Week&quot; and
&quot;Hoops of the Half&quot; will again be part of the program
format.<BR>

<P>
CHCH and the OUAA have enjoyed a history together
that exceeds 30 years. Be part of the tradition, catch the <I><B>University
Game of the Week</B></I> Saturdays at 2:00 p.m. on CHCH-TV commencing
September 7, 1996.
<HR>

<P>
<CENTER>Tentative Football Schedule</CENTER>
<HR>

<PRE>
Saturday, September  7 - Laurier @ Western    2:00 p.m.
Saturday, September 14 - York @ Laurier       2:00 p.m.
Saturday, September 21 - Windsor @ York       2:00 p.m.
Saturday, September 28 - Toronto @ Guelph     2:00 p.m.

Saturday, October    5 - Western @ Waterloo   2:00 p.m.
Saturday, October   12 - McMaster @ Guelph    2:00 p.m.
Saturday, October  *19 - York @ McMaster      2:00 p.m.
Saturday, October  *26 - Western @ Toronto    2:00 p.m.

Saturday, November   2 - Semi Final           1:00 p.m.
Saturday, November   9 - Yates Cup Final      1:00 p.m.

* These dates are tentative and are subject to change.

</PRE>

