<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News On-Line</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<P>

<CENTER>
<img src="../../images/evng_on.gif" width=400 height=56 border=0 alt="The Evening News On-Line">
</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<H1>Thursday, January 2, 1997</H1>
</CENTER>

<ul>
    <li>Cult Murder 
    <li>Police Shooting     
    <li>Evans - Court       
    <li>Flu Epidemic        
    <li>Peru - Ambassador     
    <li>Mideast Hebron      
    <li>Cowboys             
    <li>Spain Four          
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Cult Murder </b><p>
A York University graduate student appeared in court in Toronto today, charged in the stabbing death of his father.<br> 25-year-old Krister Volkmann was remanded in custody until a January 9th court appearance.<br>   He was charged with second-degree murder after his 55-year-old father, Helmuth Volkmann, was found slain in his apartment early yesterday.<br>   Toronto police say the professor had flown in from Germany on New Year's Eve.<br>   Police also say there is no evidence to prove the suspect was involved in a cult.
<hr>
<b>Police Shooting</b><p>
Friends of an Ottawa man shot four times by police believe racism was involved.<br>   They say Francis Nicholls would not have been shot and wounded yesterday afternoon if he weren't black.<br>   Nicholls was shot after officers and an ambulance crew went to his apartment because relatives couldn't reach him.<br>   Police say he had a knife but his girlfriend, who was on the phone with him at the time, is questioning the officers' behavior.
<hr>
<b>Evans - Court</b><p>
A former defence department scientist appeared briefly in court in Ottawa today on child pornography charges.<br>  46 year-old Blair Evans will reappear January 30th.<br>   He was charged last month after OPP seized more than 20-thousand computer files containing child porn at a defence department office.<br>   Evans is accused of downloading the files from the Internet.<br>   Police say they are widening their probe into the U.S. to try to determine the source of the material.
<hr>
<b>Flu Epidemic</b><p>
Much of Ontario is in the grip of the grippe.<br>   Thousands of people suffering from the influenza-a virus have swamped hospitals and clinics.<br>   Hamilton doctor Kathleen Walker says the epidemic is turning doctors' offices into "viral pits."<br>   Symptoms -- which last about a week -- include fever, sore throat, cough, fatigue and aches and pains.<br>   Children sometimes develop vomiting.<br>   Walker says there's not much physicians can do but let the bug run its course.
<hr>
<b>Peru - Ambassador</b><p>
The actions of a Canadian hero were praised in Ottawa today.<br>  Anthony Vincent is Canada's amabassador to Peru.<br>  He was in Ottawa briefing foreign affairs minister Lloyd Axworthy on the current hostage crisis.<br>  Axworthy praised Cincent for acting as a facilitator in the current hostage crisis.
<hr>
<b>Mideast Hebron</b><p>
Foreign affairs minister Lloyd Axworthy warns that the mideast peace process could fail if there is no agreement on Hebron.<br>   Israelis and Palestinians are still trying to negotiate a pullout of most Israeli troops from the west bank town.<br>   Axworthy says hebron is just one step of many that are required for peace -- but he says, it's the key step right now.
<hr>
<b>Cowboys</b><p>
Some questions are being raised about the woman who is accusing Dallas Cowboys players Erik Williams and Michael Irvin of rape.<br>  The woman's estranged husband says he doubts her story.<br>  Irvin and Williams have not been charged.<br>  And they continue to practice for Sunday's NFL playoff game versus Carolina.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Spain Four</b><p>
They were shunned in Canada, loved by the people of Spain.<br>  The Canadian veterans of the Spanish Civil War have a special place in the hearts of the people they once defended.<br>  Tonight, in our continuing series on the Spanish Civil War, veterans meet the people and discover a 60 year old debt has not been forgotten.









<P>

<CENTER><A HREF="../../intouch/"><IMG SRC="../../images/intchbd.jpg" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER =0 ALT="In Touch: Answering The Call"></A></CENTER>
<CENTER>
<P>
