<HR>

<CENTER>
<H2><A NAME="stories">Today's Business Stories</A></H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>



<CENTER>
<H1>Thursday, January 2, 1997</H1>
</CENTER>

<ul>
    <li>Economy             
    <li>Winners and Losers  
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Economy</b><p>
This recent sign of strength in the American economy was measured by the purchasing managers index which did not drop as expected.<br>  The news trigger a selloff of Canadian and U.S. bonds and contributed to a heavy selloff of U.S. and Canaian stocks early in the day.
<hr>
<b>Winners and Losers</b><p>
Just as Canadian big blue chip stocks like Bell Canada Enterprises and the major banks led Canadian stock markets to new record highs in 1996, it was also big name companies that propelled U.S. stock markets higher. Many of them were technology companies.



<P>

<CENTER><A HREF="../../intouch/"><IMG SRC="../../images/intchbd.jpg" ALT="CHCH In Touch: Answering The Call" WIDTH=515 HEIGHT=44 BORDER=0></A>
</CENTER>

<P>

