<HEAD>

<TITLE>Welcome to CHCH-TV's "Community File".</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=524 HEIGHT=85 SRC="../../images/commfile.gif" ALT="Community File Logo" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>

<P>
<B>Extending our community spirit, CHCH presents <I>Community File</I>, highlighting local
events and entertainment. </B>

<P>
<B><I>Community File</I> is seen three times each weekday on CHCH-TV: between 9:00am-10:00am, 2:00pm-3:00pm, and 4:00pm-5:00pm. </B>

<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="contributions.htm">We invite your input on Community File</A>.
</CENTER>


<CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>


<CENTER>
<H3><I>For the week of Monday, December 30, 1996</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<HR>

The Festival of Lights is almost over at Burlington's Spencer Smith Park.....so, if you haven't seen the spectacular display yet ...bundle up and stroll among the lights any night from 5pm - midnight.  Over 4000 lights...10 gallons of paint ...and 1000 feet of electrical cord were used to create the breathtaking exhibit.  
<P>
It's time to start gathering team members for the Big Brother's Bowl for Kids Sake Bowlathon.  Every team equals a new match for a child on the waiting list.  The bowlathon will take place February 15 from 1pm-4pm.  Our very own Ken Welch is chairman of this worth while event.   
<P>
Towards the Millennium is a four year partnership in the arts.  It will produce a series of musicals ...kicking off with Godspell.  It will take to the stage February 7 & 8 at Hamilton Place. 
<P>
Some other up coming performances not to miss.... enjoy an evening at the opera... Opera Hamilton will perform "Popera" January 30 and February 1.  or .... become part of ancient mythology... and attend the Canadian Stage Company's production of "Atlantis".   Its an intense ...endlessly moving.. story about a tragic love affair.   
<P>
Happy New Year.  1997 could be your lucky year ...if you bought a CNIB Lottery Calendar.  You could win any day of the year.     Calendars are still available by calling the institute.  
<P>
If you're heading out with family or meeting friends this New Year's Eve...make sure you arrive alive.  Gallop and Gallop Advertising, Sign Depot Express, Al Cosentino Remax Real Estate, CAA South Central, The Spectator, Y95 and CHCH-TV are promoting this message: don't drink and drive... decide to use or be a designated driver.  
<P>
Come join Sunni Genessco and our very own  Donna Skelly New Years Eve, as they host the 2nd Annual First Night Hamilton.  There will be an afternoon of fun for the kids and a brilliant fireworks display to bring in the new year.   First Night buttons are available at any Hamilton branch of Canada Trust, Fortino's on Dundurn, or the Sesqui Office.   Whatever your plans New Year's Eve...make sure you arrive alive ...  Don't drink and drive. Decide to use or be a designated driver.  




