<HEAD>

<TITLE>Crime Stoppers Crime Of The Week</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER>
<TABLE border =0 cellpading=5>

<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="../../images/crimlogo.gif"></TD>
<TD><H1>Crime<BR>of<BR>the<BR>Week</H1></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>

<HR>
<CENTER><H1>Crime Stoppers #710: Break, Enter and Theft</H1></CENTER>
<HR>

Crime Stoppers and the Hamilton-Wentworth Regional Police need 
your help in solving a break, enter and theft.
<P>
On Monday, November 25, 1996, shortly after 3:00am, Johnny 
Kools Bar and Grill was entered by thieves who took a RCA VCR, a 
Pioneer tuner, many compact discs and cassettes, various electronic and 
sound equipment and a quantity of lottery tickets.  There were no 
signs of forced entry.
<P>
A security surveillance camera has captured at least two suspects 
carrying property down an alley, from the rear of the premises.
<P>
The two suspects are described as white males, in their mid 20's 
to mid 30's, average height and build.
<P>

<H3>If you have any information about this break and enter, or information
on any other serious crime call Hamilton-Wentworth Crime Stoppers
at (905) 522-TIPS. That's (905) 522-8477 to be eligible for a
cash reward of up to $1,000. 
<P>
Remember, in all cases, you will
not have to reveal your identity. Crime Stoppers does not subscribe
to Call Display.</H3>



<HR>

<P>

<CENTER>
<I>CHCH and Hamilton Wentworth Regional Police want your help
in solving a crime!</I></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><I>See crimes reenacted each Monday on CHCH News.</I></CENTER>
