<HEAD>

<TITLE>CHCH Production Services: The Discovery Mobile</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<HR>
<CENTER><H1><I>The Discovery Mobile</I></H1></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
Discovery is the latest addition to CHCH TVs mobile fleet. This
audio mobile employs state-of-the-art technology which includes,
two 24-track digital multitracks, a sophisticated computer-automated
console, flexible powering and communications in a spacious, yet
efficient, environment.
<P>
With elegant interfacing to various venues a main design criteria,
the mobile is equally at home when connected to a television studio,
an outdoor sporting event, or a concert hall. Discovery's large
inventory of equipment combined with CHCH-TVs immense supply of
facilities and world-class audio engineers - translates into a
service that can provide maximum versatility and an excellent
final product. 
<P>
The unique live broadcast suite, located at the rear of the truck,
allows for separate control over a stereo program feed while allowing
the main control room to concentrate on multitrack recording and
mix down. The truck interior may also be utilized as production
space for editing, voice-overs, graphics, etc., and could be integrated
with a television mobile facility, or function independently.
Discovery Mobile is one of the premier mobile sound facilities
in North America, but is capable of working in other applications
such as film and television production as well. 
<P>
<I><B>Equipment:</B></I>
<P>
<B>CONSOLE:</B>
<UL>
<LI>AMEK &quot;Mozart&quot; automated recording console
<LI>52 mic and line input channels
<LI>1 Stereo Output, 32 buss outputs, 16 aux buss outputs
<LI>12 external DAs over and above busses
<LI>computer-controlled grouping and routing
</UL>

<P>
<B>RECORDERS:</B>
<UL>
<LI>2 Sony PCM-3324 Digital 24-track recorders
<LI>1 Fostex D20 stereo RDAT recorder
<LI>1 Otari MX-55 1/4&quot; stereo analog recorder
<LI>1 Yamaha C-300 cassette recorder
</UL>

<P>
<I>Other available equipment:</I> 
<UL>
<LI>2 Studer A810 stereo analog recorders
<LI>1 Ampex MM1200 16-track recorder
<LI>1 Fostex D20 stereo RDAT digital recorder
<LI>1 Sony DTC-75ES RDAT digital recorder 
</UL>

<P>
<B>PROCESSORS:</B>
<UL>
<LI>AKG 68K4 digital reverb
<LI>Yamaha REV-5 digital reverb
<LI>Yamaha SPX-1000 digital effects
<LI>Yamaha SPX-90 digital effects
<LI>Eventide H3000 digital effects
<LI>12 BSS compressor/limiters
<LI>12 BSS noise gates
<LI>2 Aphex stereo compellors
</UL>

<P>
<I>Other available equipment:</I>
<UL>
<LI>Lexicon 224 digital reverb
<LI>Lexicon 300 digital reverb
<LI>Eventide H3000 SE digital effects
<LI>Aphex Stereo Aural Exciter Type III
<LI>Aphex Stereo Compellor 320
<LI>4 Valley Gatex noise gates
</UL>

<P>
<B>MICROPHONES:</B>
<UL>
<LI>6 Shure SM57
<LI>6 Shure SM 58
<LI>30 AKG 452EB
<LI>4 AKG 451 EB
<LI>4 AKG 224
<LI>5 Sennheiser MKH 406
<LI>5 EV RE 20
<LI>1 AKG D12E
<LI>4 AKG 747
<LI>1 Audio Technica AT825 Stereo mic
<LI>2 Neumann U87
<LI>4 Crown 6LM 100
<LI>3 Crown 6LM 200
<LI>2 Crown PZM 30GPB
<LI>1 Crown PZM 315
<LI>4 Sennheiser ME80
<LI>7 Sennheiser MKH 816
<LI>2 Sennheiser MKH 815
<LI>2 Sennheiser MKH 416
<LI>8 Sony ECM 77 Lavaliers
</UL>

<P>
<I>plus a variety of Wireless &amp; Dynamic microphones</I>
<P>
<B>AUDIO SWEETENING</B>:
<UL>
<LI>fully programmed sampler ready for audience applause &amp;
laff-tracks
<LI>AKAI S1100 Sampler with S1100 EX memory expansion
<LI>Dynatek MO Drive
</UL>

<P>
<B>INTERCOM:</B>
<UL>
<LI>Telex Audiocom - up to 50 stations on 4 channels
<LI>3 stations in truck
<LI>2 speaker, 4 headset remote stations
<LI>Interface capabilities with RTS, Clearcom, dedicated or dial-up
phone lines and most other 2- or 4-wire intercom systems 
</UL>

<P>
<I>Other available equipment:</I>
<UL>
<LI>RTS Telex Wireless Base-Station - 4 headset stations
<LI>Comtec Wireless IFB
<LI>Hardwired IFBs
</UL>

<P>
<B>VIDEO:</B> 
<UL>
<LI>1 Sony 28&quot; colour monitor/TV
<LI>2 NEC 12&quot; colour monitors
<LI>1 Sony low-light camera
<LI>video switchers, hum rejection, video distribution amps
</UL>

<P>
<I>Other available equipment:</I>
<UL>
<LI>as required through CHCH TVs unlimited video facilities
</UL>

<P>
<B>BROADCAST:</B>
<UL>
<LI>D&amp;R 8 input, stereo out console
<LI>Yamaha 8 input, stereo out console
<LI>Otari MX-55 1/4&quot; stereo recorder
<LI>3-slot cartridge recorder/player
<LI>Technics SL P1300 Broadcast CD player
</UL>

<P>
<B>INTERCONNECTION:</B>
<UL>
<LI>2 100M 48 channel microphone snakes
<LI>48 input stage mic box, with 32 Jensen 3-way transformer mic
splits
<LI>30 additional mic splits, with 3-way Hammond transformers
<LI>connection bulkhead for extra inputs, outputs, video, intercoms,
timecode &amp; phonelines 
<LI><I>Other available equipment:</I>
<LI>over 2000' of 12 channel Canair snake
<LI>over 3000' of various snakes
</UL>

<P>
<B>BODY:</B>
<UL>
<LI>28' custom aluminum, with storage under floor, and rear camera
deck
</UL>

<P>
<B>CHASSIS:</B>
<UL>
<LI>1991 Freightliner Cab Over Engine, 240 HP Diesel
<LI>Air-ride Suspension
</UL>

<P>
<B>AIR-CONDITIONING:</B>
<UL>
<LI>2 Bard heat/cool units, low velocity insulated ducts
</UL>

<P>
<B>POWER:</B>
