<HEAD>
<TITLE>Star Trek: The Exhibit</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#F9DF27" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#4A3F93">

<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="startrek2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

<HR>

Don't miss this exciting display of original Star Trek exhibits from the television series and movies.  This is the largest ever exhibition from the TV series in the world.
<P>
The 12,000 square foot exhibition features:
<UL>
<LI><H1>Star Trek <I>the classic series</I></H1>
<UL>
<LI>A model of the U.S.S. Enterprise NCC 1701
<LI>An audio-visual introduction
<LI>Full-size Bridge from the original Star Trek
<LI>Costumes and props
<LI>Mr. Spock's science rank costume from the classic series
<LI>Dr. McCoy's medical kit
</UL>

<P>

<LI><H1>Star Trek <I>the Next Generation</I></H1>
<UL>
<LI>Picard's ready room, desk and chair
<LI>Full-size set of the transporter deck
</UL>

<P>

<LI><H1>Star Trek <I>the Movies</I></H1>
<UL>
<LI>The Klingons, including Klingon Throne
<LI>Costumes and weapons
<LI>Kirk's chair and green command rank tunic worn by William Shatner
<LI>Mr. Spock's favourite Tricorder scientific instrument and Vulcan ceremonial robe
</UL>

<P>

<LI><H1>Star Trek <I>Deep Space Nine</I> and <I>Voyager</I></H1>
<UL>
<LI>Simulation Reactor
<LI>Odo's Monument
<LI>Back-lit mural of the Deep Space Nine station
</UL>

</UL>


<CENTER><H1><A HREF="http://www.trekcanada.com/">For more details on this exciting world-class event, visit the Star Trek: The Exhibit Home Page.</A></H1></CENTER>

<P>

<CENTER><A HREF="../sites/"><IMG SRC="../images/web_bar.jpg" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER =0 ALT="Explore the Web with CHCH In Touch"></A></CENTER>
