<TITLE>James Macdonald Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/james.gif">
<H1>President, C.E.O.</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>James Macdonald has enjoyed nearly twenty years of experience in
various aspects of the entertainment industry.    Before assuming the
position of President and CEO of CHCH, Mr. Macdonald held the position
of Vice-President  of Sales and Regulatory Affairs at CFMT Television.

<P>Prior to that position, Mr. Macdonald was Manager of Special
Projects and New Business Development for Rogers  Broadcasting Limited.

<P> His career began in the recording industry as a promotion
representative with London Records, which led Mr.  Macdonald to the
positions of Ontario Promotion Manager at Capital Records EMI Canada
Ltd. and General Manager of Arista Records.

<P>Mr. Macdonald sits on the Board of Directors for such organizations
as Doctors Hospital, Chedoke-McMaster  Hospitals, Television Bureau of
Canada and is a founding Director of the Real Therrien Foundation. </P> 

<P>Jim and his wife Andrea Watley have two children, Alexandra who is 6,
and Fraser who is 4.

<P>Send Jim Macdonald an E-Mail message here: <A HREF="mailto:jmac@tor.hookup.net">president@chch.wic.ca</A><P>

