<HEAD>
<TITLE>Reg McGuire Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/regm.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=144 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>

<P>Reg McGuire Executive Vice President and General Manager CHCH-TV 
Born in Montreal, Quebec in 1936, Reg McGuire briefly resided in that
city before his family  moved to Alma and eventually Hopetown -- both in
the province of Quebec.  At the age of eight,  his family settled in
Kapuskasing, Ontario, where he completed his public and high school 
education.   He then travelled to Toronto where he attended Ryerson
Polytechnical Institute and  graduated from Radio and Television Arts.

<P>His broadcasting career began in 1957 at CHAT-TV in Medicine Hat,
Alberta.  During his three  year stay at the station, Mr. McGuire worked
as an on-air operator followed by the post of  electronic maintenance
technician.

<P>On June 6, 1960, Reg McGuire joined CHCH-TV as a telecine operator,
then cameraman.  A  year later, he moved into the position of Technical
Director for both studios and mobiles.  In  1973, he became Operations
Manager.  Management, recognizing his integrity and leadership  talents,
promoted him to the position of Vice President, Operations and
Production in 1988.   Later that same year, Mr. McGuire was promoted to
Vice President and General Manager.

<P>In November, 1994, Reg McGuire became Executive Vice-President and
General Manager of  CHCH-TV, a reflection of the significant
contributions he has made to the station over the years.

<P>An active member in the community, Mr. McGuire holds many committee
and board positions.   They include Chairman of the Advisory Committee
for Niagara College's Radio Television and Film Program, member of the
Advisory Committee of Mohawk College's  Television Program,  member of
the Board of Directors of Chedoke-McMaster Hospitals Foundation,
Co-Executive Producer of the CHCH/Chedoke-McMaster Children's Hospital 
Mother's Day Telethon, member Board of Directors Hamilton Chamber of
Commerce, member  Board of Directors of the Canadian Broadcasters
Retransmission  Rights Agency (CBRA), member of Board of Niagara College
Foundation.  As well Mr. McGuire  is a member of Hamilton YMCA,
Wilderness Canoe Club, and Ancaster Veteran's Slo-Pitch  Softball
League.

<P>Mr. McGuire resides in Ancaster with his wife, Brenda. He is the
proud father of one son and equally proud grandfather of two.
                                                       

<P>Send Reg McGuire an E-Mail message here: <A HREF="mailto:gm@chch.wic.ca">gm@chch.wic.ca</A>
<P>
