<HEAD>

<TITLE>Neil MacLean Biography</TITLE>

</HEAD>
<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/neilm.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=117 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>


<P>Neil MacLean, CHCH-TV's Vice President, Finance, was born in Whitehorse, Yukon, 
December 26, 1949. As his father was a member of the Air Force, Mr. MacLean had the 
opportunity to travel extensively while growing up, and lived in such
cities as Winnipeg,  Toronto, Hamilton, and the town of Greenwood, Nova
Scotia.

<P>Following high school, Mr. MacLean attended Hamilton's McMaster
University and  graduated in 1973 with a Bachelor of Commerce degree. 
That same year, Mr. MacLean  began his professional career at Price
Waterhouse.  In 1976, he received his Chartered  Accountant designation.

<P>While at Price Waterhouse, he quickly progressed from articling
student to job senior to  supervisor.  In 1979, Otis Elevator hired him
as their Accounting Coordinator.  Next,  Columbus McKinnon caught Mr.
MacLean's attention and, in 1981, he moved over to  become that
company's Controller.  Impressed with Mr. MacLean's track record, CHCH-
TV offered him the position of Controller at the station, a position he
held from 1983 to  1987, the year he was promoted to his current
position -- Vice President, Finance.

<P>Mr. MacLean is a member of the Financial Executives Institute,
Hamilton Chapter, as well  as a member of the Board of Directors of the
Alzheimer Society of Halton-Wentworth.

<P>The proud father of three daughters enjoys listening to rock and
roll music and  participating in such lively activities as hockey,
baseball, cycling, and tennis. 


