<HEAD>

<TITLE>James Mercer Biography</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/jimmer.gif" WIDTH=523 HEIGHT=145 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>

<P>James Mercer, CHCH-TV's Vice President, Engineering, was born in
Edinburgh, Scotland in  1937, and educated at Boroughmuir Senior
Secondary School.

<P>As an employee of the British Post Office (1954 to 1966) in the
field of radio and television  communications, Mr. Mercer completed
courses at the Post Office training school in  Staffordshire, England,
as well as with the City and Guilds of London.

<P>In 1966, Mr. Mercer came to Canada and joined CHCH-TV.  Seven years
later he was appointed  to the position of Director of Engineering, and
in 1988 he was made Vice President of Engineering.

<P>James Mercer is a member of the Society of Motion Picture and
Television Engineers, and  served on the Board of Managers for this
organization's Toronto section for two terms.  He is  also a member, and
Past President, of the Association of Central Canada Broadcast
Engineers,  Technologists and Technicians.
