<HEAD>

<TITLE>Engineering Notes</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1><CENTER>CHCH Engineering Notes</CENTER></H1>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/sat.gif"></CENTER><HR>

<P>
On May 29, 1995 we completed the installation of a new, completely
solid state, transmitter. This was purchased from Larcan, a world
leader, and Canada's premier manufacturer, of high power solid
state television transmitters.
<P>
The CHCH transmitter site is located on the Niagara Escarpment,
over looking Hamilton, Stoney Creek and Burlington, at the extreme
west end of Lake Ontario. With an antenna towering 1497ft above
Lake Ontario and an effective radiated power of 325,000 watts,
our signal reaches millions of viewers in southwestern Ontario
and western New York State on channel 11. In addition, our signal
is available in communities coast to coast in Canada via satellite.
This service is provided by CANCOM, one of our sister companies.


<P>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
