<HEAD>

<TITLE>CHCH Ownership</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/11s.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER><H1>CHCH-TV's Ownership</H1></CENTER>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

<P>Since January 1, 1993, CHCH has been owned by WIC Western International Communications
Ltd. through Westcom TV Group Ltd.   WIC Western International
Communications Ltd. is an integrated Canadian communications,
broadcast and entertainment company with its head office in Vancouver,
British Columbia.  

<P>WIC is the only Canadian broadcasting company
operating in television, pay television, radio and satellite network
services.  WIC owns eight television and eleven radio stations across Canada
and is a shareholder in the CTV Television Network.    Through Westcom
Entertainment Group Ltd. and Allarcom Creative Development, WIC is
involved in the development  and production of films and television
programs for sale in Canadian and foreign markets.  WIC operates three
radio networks and is involved in national advertising sales -- in
television through full ownership of Western Broadcast Sales Ltd., and
in radio through a 50 percent interest in Canadian Broadcast Sales.  WIC
is the pay television licensee in Western Canada for Superchannel and
Home Theatre, a pay-per-view service.  WIC also owns 50 percent of the
Family Channel.  As well WIC owns 53.7 percent of Canadian Satellite
Communications Inc. (Cancom).  In 1993, WIC acquired an option for the
exclusive Canadian rights to an innovative cellular distribution
technology for television, telephone, radio and data signals called
CellularVision. 

<CENTER><H2>Previous Ownership</H2></CENTER>

<BR> (1) Local Consortium consisting of: Maple Leaf Broadcasting,
Wentworth Broadcasting and Southam Press       (ownership divided in 1/3
shares)
<BR> (2)  Theatre Properties Hamilton Ltd. joined the above       
(ownership divided into 1/4 shares)
<BR> (3)  Selkirk Communications Ltd.
<BR>(4)  Maclean Hunter Ltd.
<BR>(5)  WIC Western International Communications Ltd.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
