<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Dangerous Minds", New This Fall on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<P>

<CENTER><IMG HEIGHT=96 WIDTH=504 SRC="../../images/fall96.gif"></CENTER>

<CENTER>
<H1><I><B>Dangerous Minds</B></I></H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
Based on the hit movie of the same name, which starred Michelle
Pfeiffer, and memoirs of the real Louanne Johnson, <B>Annie Potts
</B>now takes on the role of the passionate, impious, nonconformist
teacher who touches students' lives in a racially pressured, inner-city
school system .  Tirelessly battling the school's jaded administration
and trying to excite her students about learning, Louanne's biggest
challenge comes when her kids leave the classroom and face overwhelming
personal struggles.  
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 BORDER=0>
<H3><B><I>Dangerous Minds</I></B> on the WEB:</H3>
</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<A HREF="http://www.abctelevision.com/fall/html/danger/dangfram.html">The <I>Dangerous Minds</I> Page at ABC</A>
<BR>

</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>
<P>

<I>Credits for</I><B> <I>Dangerous Minds</I></B><I>:</I> <B> </B>
<P>
Comedienne<B> Annie Potts</B> (<I>Designing Women</I>) stars.
 The movie's Oscar-winning writer <B>Ron Bass</B> (<I>Rain Man</I>)
is re-teamed with producer <B>Jerry Bruckheimer</B> (<I>The Rock,
Top Gun, Crimson Tide</I>) who share executive producer duties
with Diane Frolov and Andrew Schneider. Production Company: Touchstone
Television/Simpson/Bruckheimer Films.
<P>

