<HEAD>
<TITLE>"The Nanny," on CHCH-TV</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../images/prog_pri.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>

<P>
<CENTER><H1><B><I>The Nanny</I></B></H1></CENTER>

<CENTER><H5>
<A HREF="nannyfd.htm">Fran Drescher as Fran Fine</A> | <A HREF="nannycs.htm">Charles Shaughnessy as Maxwell Sheffield</A><BR>

<A HREF="nannydd.htm">Daniel Davis as Niles</A> | <A HREF="nannynt.htm">Nicholle Tom as Maggie Sheffield</A><BR>

<A HREF="nannybs.htm">Benjamin Salisbury as Brighton Sheffield</A> | <A HREF="nannymz.htm">Madeline Zima as Grace Sheffield</A><BR>

</H5>
</CENTER>

<HR>

<P>
Fran Drescher stars as Fran Fine, a street-smart young woman,
with a face out of Vogue and a voice out of Queens, in <I><B>The
Nanny</B></I>, a half-hour comedy series.
<P>
Fran, fresh out of her job as a bridal consultant in her boyfriend's
shop is working as a door-to-door cosmetics saleswoman when she
stumbles onto the opportunity to become nanny to the children
of a wealthy Broadway producer, Maxwell Sheffield (Charles Shaughnessy).
Once Fran realizes Sheffield is not only wealthy but also a widower,
she eagerly takes the job.
<P>
It's a situation of blue collar meets blue blood, as Fran gives
the prim-and-proper Maxwell and his problem children a dose of
&quot;Queens logic,&quot; helping them become a healthy, happy
family.
<P>
Fran discovers she's got a lot of work to do with the three Sheffield
youngsters. Maggie (Nicholle Tom) is a pretty, yet insecure teenager
in need of a boost in self esteem. Convinced he doesn't need a
nanny, Brighton (Benjamin Salisbury) is a master at mischievous
pranks and tormenting his sisters. Six-year-old Grace (Madeline
Zima) is a serious child who dotes on her daily sessions with
her therapist.
<P>
Proudly running the Sheffield household is the butler Niles (Daniel
Davis), who watches all events with a bemused eye and levels problems
with his quick wit. Niles quickly recognizes Fran's gift at bringing
warmth back to the family. C.C. Babcock (Lauren Lane), Maxwell's
socialite business partner, views Fran with a mixture of skepticism
and jealousy, as she has designs on the very available Sheffield
herself
<P>
Robert Sternin and Prudence Fraser are executive producers on
<I><B>The Nanny</B></I>. Peter Marc Jacobson, Pam Eells and Sally
Lapidus are co-executive producers. Kathy Landsberg and Fran Drescher
are producers.
<HR>

<P>
<I><B>The Nanny</B></I> is a half-hour comedy series produced
by Sternin/Fraser Ink., Inc. in association with TriStar Television,
distributed by Columbia TriStar International Television. 
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
