<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Pearl", New This Fall on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<P>

<CENTER><IMG HEIGHT=96 WIDTH=504 SRC="../../images/fall96.gif"></CENTER>

<CENTER>
<H1><I><B>Pearl</B></I></H1>
</CENTER>


<P>

<B>Rhea Perlman</B> (<I>Cheers</I>) stars as a mature, outspoken,
working-class widow who is determined to graduate from the hallowed
halls and ivy-covered walls of Yale University
-- but first, she must deflect the prickly assertions hurled by
the ever-revered and feared, pompous Professor Pynchon, played
by <B>Malcom McDowell</B> ( <I>A Clockwork Orange, Star Trek:
Generations</I>).  In so doing, she wins the approval of her fellow
students, which include an insecure genius and dedicated intellectual.
 Her most arduous test, however, is convincing her electronics
store co-workers that her pursuit in academia is not a passing
fancy.     
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 BORDER=0>
<H3><B><I>Pearl</I></B> on the WEB:</H3>
</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<A HREF="http://www.cbs.com/primetime/pearl.html">The <I>Pearl</I> at CBS</A>
<BR>

</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>
<P>

<I>Credits for<B> Pearl</B>:<B>  </B></I>
<P>
<B>Rhea Perlman</B> (<I>Cheers</I>), <B>Malcolm McDowell</B> (
<I>A Clockwork Orange</I>, <I>If</I>, <I>Star Trek: Generations</I>),
<B>Carol Kane </B>(<I>Taxi</I>) and <B>Kevin Corrigan</B> (<I>GoodFellas</I>)
star.  Don Reo, Paul Junger Witt, Tony Thomas, Gary S. Levine
and Rhea Perlman are executive producers; Director: James Burrows.
 <I><B>Pearl</B></I><B> </B>is a Witt-Thomas Production.
       
<P>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 BORDER=0><BR>
<A HREF="../../sites/programs.htm">Your Favorite Programs on the Web: Visit our Program Sites Page!</A><BR>
