<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Mr. Rhodes", New This Fall on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<P>

<CENTER><IMG HEIGHT=96 WIDTH=504 SRC="../../images/fall96.gif"></CENTER>

<CENTER>
<H1><I><B>Mr. Rhodes</B></I></H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
Stand-up comedian <B>Tom Rhodes</B> stars as a long-haired, free-thinking
scholar and author, who escaped his blue-collar upbringing for
the promise of literary success and excitement in New York City.
 Since inspiration has been an infrequent visitor, Tom returns
to his hometown to teach at the very prep school he enthusiastically
ridiculed during his years there as a student.  Tom's unorthodox<I>
</I>teaching methods send the headmaster reeling, 
mortifies his elitist colleagues and wins the approval of the
student body.  Sharing Tom's discomfort in a confining prep school
environment is the sexy, edgy Nikki Harkin -- the girl he worshipped
from afar during his high school days.  Between his headmaster,
the students and Nikki's fiancee, Tom is the one who ends up getting
an education!


<HR>

<I>Credits for <B>Mr. Rhodes</B>:</I>
<P>
<B>Tom Rhodes, Farrah Forke, Stephen Tobolowsky, Ron Glass</B>
and <B>Jessica Stone</B> star.  Executive Producer: Peter Noah
(<I>Anything But Love</I>); Executive Producers/Creators/Writers:
Mark Brazill (<I>In Living Color</I>), Jennifer Heath (<I>Roseanne</I>);
Director: Peter Bonerz (<I>Murphy Brown</I>).  Production Company:
NBC Studios in association with Universal Television. 
       
<P>
