<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Life With Roger", New This Fall on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<P>

<CENTER><IMG HEIGHT=96 WIDTH=504 SRC="../../images/fall96.gif"></CENTER>

<CENTER>
<H1><I><B>Life With Roger</B></I></H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
On the day he is to be wed, Jason meets a peculiar, yet lovable
stranger, Roger, who throws himself into his life and turns it
into a wild adventure.  First, Roger gives Jason the courage to
leave his loudmouth bride at the altar -- a woman he could not
tolerate in the first place!  Next, the two new &quot;friends&quot;
(it's not a mutual feeling) agree to share an apartment.  As the
duo is completely mismatched in character, what ensues is a series
of  hilarious situations.  It's clear to see Jason's world goes
through a complete turn-a-round as he discovers <I><B>Life With
Roger</B></I>.
<P>
<HR>
<I>Credits for<B> Life With Roger</B>:</I>
<P>
<B>Mike O'Malley</B> (host of <I>Guts</I>) stars as Roger along
with <B>Maurice Godin </B>and <B>Hallie Todd</B>.  Executive Producers:
Bob Griffard and Howard Adler (<I>Step By Step, Perfect Strangers</I>);
Producer: Deborah Oppenheimer; Director: Barnet Kellman.  
       
