<HEAD>
<TITLE>Dan McLean Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<IMG SRC="../../images/dan.gif">

<P>In his 23 years with CHCH-TV, DAN McLEAN has become one of the most
seasoned and credible  anchors in the Southern Ontario broadcast market.</P>

<P>Hailing from Welland, Ontario, Dan began his journey down the broadcast
career path before he finished  high school.  While still in grade 11,
he worked at CHOW Radio in Welland.  After a brief year spent  pursuing
a Bachelor of Science Degree at the University of Western Ontario,
London, Dan returned to  radio.  He collected valuable experience at a
number of stations throughout Ontario and Saskatchewan,  eventually
entering the television field along the way.</P>

<P>Dan McLean has
contributed greatly to CHCH-TV since his arrival in 1972.  Beginning as
a commercial  booth-announcer and back-up anchor, he quickly went on to
become the host of "MidDay," "New Faces,"  and then news anchor for the
6:00pm and 11:00pm newscasts.  Currently, he co-anchors the Channel 11 
News At Noon as well as First Edition at 5:30pm.</P>

<P>In addition to
his newsroom responsibilities, Dan is very involved within the community
in the Hamilton  area, serving on numerous committees.  He was the first
Honourary Chairman for Year of the Child,  Honourary Chairman for the
Hamilton-Wentworth Kidney Foundation, Honourary Chairman for the Red 
Cross Side By Side Fundraising Campaign, and is former President of the
Hamilton Press Club.  Dan is  currently the 1995 United Way Campaign
Chairman.</P>

<P>Married with three children, Dan enjoys a number of
interests in his spare time, among them: carpentry,  sailing, skiing,
squash, hockey, pets and motorcycles.</P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="mailto:anchors@chch.wic.ca">Send Dan McLean a message here.</A></CENTER><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
