<HEAD>
<TITLE>Paul Hendrick Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<IMG SRC="../../images/paul.gif">

<P> Before becoming CHCH-TV's play by play man for the University Game
of the Week, among other  responsibilities, PAUL HENDRICK had already
done a lot of "travelling."   Born in Sudbury in October  of 1956, Paul
grew up in Noranda, Quebec.  After graduating from high school in
Mississauga, this  geologist's son obtained a Political Science Degree
from the University of Toronto.

<P> Paul's broadcasting career began
in 1979 in Sault Ste Marie.  Two years later, he made the move to 
CHCH-TV where he perfected his craft on weekends.  Paul is currently a
regular weekday fixture on  CHCH-TV's News at Noon, First Edition at
5:30 p.m., and Community File.   Since 1985, he has been the  play by
play man for the OUAA, University Game of the Week, weekends.

<P>Always
one to be involved in the community, Paul is the Honourary Chairman of
the annual CNIB Glo- Ball Golf Tournament, which benefits visually
challenged kids.  As well, he is the media chairman of the  1996 World
Curling Championships  set to take place in Hamilton.  He was also a
Director for the 1990  Memorial Cup Hockey Championship.

<P>Paul and
his wife are the proud parents of a beautiful daughter.

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

