<HEAD>
<TITLE>Maria Hayes Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<IMG SRC="../../images/maria.gif">

<P>Born in Ancaster, Maria attended highshool in Hamilton and later
went on to Mohawk College to pursue studies in Television Broadcasting.

<P>
Maria began her career as a radio reporter and newscaster, landing
her first job in 1985, at CKDK in Woodstock, Ontario. For the
next two years, Maria refined her reporting skills at stations
in Hamilton and Brantford. In 1987, she entered the world of television
at CKNX in Wingham, Ontario, acting as both producer and anchor
of the eleven o'clock news. Maria joined the team at <B>CHCH-TV</B>
in 1989 as a reporter. Today, she is the anchor/producer of the
weekend news.

<P>
Maria Hayes has proven on more than one occasion that work and
play do indeed go together. She jumped out of a plane at 10,000
feet to promote the Hamilton Air show and also had the experience
of playing Copps and Robbers at the OPP Shooting Range in Aurora.

<P>
Ms. Hayes is not only sister to <B>CHCH-TV</B>'s weatherman, Matt
Hayes, but she is also married to one her co-workers, Scott Urquhart,
a reporter for <B>CHCH-TV</B>. Together, they have two children,
Tessa and Reid.<BR>

<P>
When Maria is not having &quot;fun&quot; at work, she enjoys exercising
and spending time with her kids. She also loves to cook and is
an avid antique collector.<BR>


