<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Donna Skelly Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<IMG SRC="../../images/donna.gif">

<P> CHCH's DONNA SKELLY was born in the northern town of Capreol,
Ontario in 1961.

<P>Following her high school days in Sudbury,
Ontario, Donna studied Radio and TV Arts at Toronto's  Seneca College
and began her broadcasting Career in 1982 in radio, at CHIP FM in Fort
Coulonge,  Quebec.

<P>Over the years, Donna has worked in a number of
stations throughout Ontario and Quebec.  As a reporter,  she has covered
everything from the prison riots at Joyceville in Kingston to the
Canadian Forces  involvement in the Gulf War in Qatar.

<P>In 1983,
Donna accepted an opportunity in television, at CHRO TV/Radio in
Pembroke, Ontario for News  reporting and anchoring.  Two years later,
Donna was reporting and anchoring the 6:00pm newscast in  Kingston,
Ontario at CKWS TV/Radio.

<P>Impressed with her capabilities, CHCH brought Donna on board in
1988.  Since that time, she has  held the dual position of co-anchor and
producer of Newsroom 11 Mid-Day and most recently for the  Channel 11
Evening News, weeknights at 6:00pm.

<P>Regular workouts help Donna
keep pace with her busy schedule both personally and professionally.  
When not at work or volunteering her services to many charitable
organizations as a concerned citizen, Donna enjoys traveling with her
husband Rino, and spending time with her children.
<P>
