<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>George Szostak Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<IMG SRC="../../images/george.gif">

<P> GEORGE SZOSTAK has been with CHCH since 1979 and has become one of
the most informative and highly regarded business reporters in Southern
Ontario today.

<P> A graduate of Mohawk College's Broadcast
Journalism program, George worked as a general assignment  reporter in
Northeastern Ontario and Northwestern Quebec before coming to CHCH.

<P>Beginning as a General Assignment reporter at CHCH, he covered may of
the economic, financial and labor news stories that were the result of
the 1981-82 recession and the recovery that followed.  The  recession
also created a demand among Canadians for more economic and financial
news on a regular  basis.  In 1988 George was assigned to report
exclusively on business and the economy and to prepare and  read a
nightly business report on CHCH.

<P> A wealth of information, the
Business Report includes a brief summary of the day's developments in 
financial markets, nightly quotations of the New York and Toronto Stock
Exchanges, precious metals  prices and oil prices, the daily value of
the Canadian Dollar and other major currencies, profiles of  Hamilton
and area business, and interviews with economists and industry
specialists.  Friday's "Best Buy"  investment segment usually generates
calls from interested viewers when a Hamilton-area investment  dealer
offers specific recommendations for a specific investor profile.

<P>The Business Report with George Szostak airs Monday to Friday at 6:15pm on
the Channel 11 Evening  News, and is repeated during Channel 11 News
Final Edition at 11:45pm.

<P>George is a past President of the
Canadian Association of Broadcast Employees, a title which he held for 
four years.  He is also active in the Hamilton and District Chamber of
Commerce Annual Business  Achievement Awards.
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

