<HEAD>
<TITLE>Fred Anderton Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<IMG SRC="../../images/fred.gif">

<P>FRED ANDERTON received his elementary and secondary education in
Barrie, Ontario, where he was born on February 21, 1948.   In 1971, Fred
graduated from Hamilton's McMaster University with a  Bachelor of Arts
Degree.

<P> Before his arrival at CHCH-TV in June of 1979, Fred
honed his broadcasting skills, first, as a news  reporter for CKBB
Radio, Barrie, starting in 1977.   In May of 1978, Fred moved over to
CFTJ Radio,  Cambridge, where he took on news responsibilities as well
as the duties of News and Sports director.   Since CHCH-TV lured him
away from Cambridge in 1979, Fred has been a permanent on-air
personality  on the station's newscasts as a sports reporter and most
recently as sports anchor on The Evening News at  6:00 p.m.

<P>The
annual fundraiser, The Juan Guzman Celebrity Golf Classic, which
benefits the Children's Hospital at  Chedoke-McMaster, was initiated by
Fred Anderton in 1994, and Fred remains the tournament chair.

<P> In
his spare time, Fred enjoys golf, slo-pitch and coaching minor baseball.
 Fred and his wife have struck a perfect balance with regards to their
family life.  They have four children - - two girls and two boys.

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

