<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Tony Parsons Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<IMG SRC="../../images/tony.gif">  

<P>BCTV's Vice-President of News/Public Affairs, TONY PARSONS was born in Gosport,
England.  In  1948, Tony and his family settled in Feversham, Ontario.

<P>After completing school studies in Feversham, Kitchener, and Sarnia,
Tony took his high school  counselor's advice and investigated a career
in broadcasting.  He enrolled in Radio and Television at Toronto's
Ryerson Polytechnical Institute.

<P>Tony's broadcasting career began
in a Stratford, Ontario radio station, CJCS.  Before taking his first 
television job as a reporter, his voice was also heard in Guelph on
CJOY, in Hamilton on CHML, and  finally Toronto on CHUM.

<P> His
news style caught the attention of CFTO-TV, Toronto, where he worked his
way up the ladder to  become the stations' late evening news anchor. 
Eight years later, Tony took a posting in Vancouver as the  West Coast
correspondent for the CTV National News.

<P>In 1975, Tony Parsons joined BCTV in Vancouver to take over the
6:00pm anchor assignment.  He has  occupied the anchor desk during the
dinner hour for the past 20 years.

<P> Tony accepted the dual role
of News Director/Anchor at BCTV in 1989, and in 1990, was appointed
Vice-President of News. 

<P>Beginning in September 1993, Tony began
anchoring a new national newscast - "Canada Tonight," based  in the BCTV
studios in Vancouver.  "Canada Tonight" draws from the coast-to-coast
resources of the  Westcom TV Group; delivering all the major stories
from across Canada, weeknights at 6:30pm.

<P> Tony divides his time
between a summer home on Bowen Island, a ski condo in Whistler, and a
town  home in Kitsilano.  Tony likes to spend his free time golfing,
reading, fishing, picking away at classical guitar, and traveling.   He
also freely gives of his time to numerous charitable organizations.

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
