<HEAD>
<TITLE>Jennifer Mossop Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<IMG SRC="../../images/jennifer.gif">  

<P>CHCH-TV news
anchor JENNIFER MOSSOP was born during the month of June in Toronto,
Ontario.   Her first few years of school were spent at a Toronto French
school, but when the family moved in 1967,  Jennifer completed her
primary, secondary and post-secondary education in London, Ontario,
ultimately  graduating from Fanshawe College in Broadcast Journalism.  A
few years later, her interest in the  continuation of learning, as well
as her love for the French language, took her to Universite De Toulon, 
France, for the summer of 1986.

<P> While still rooted in London,
Jennifer began her broadcast career at CJBK Radio as a reporter and 
newscaster.  In 1981, CHCH-TV hired her to be the Niagara Bureau Chief,
a position she held until 1986.   Recognizing her exceptional talents, 
the station moved Jennifer into the seat of weekend news anchor in 
1987.  In 1990,  Jennifer left her weekend duties to produce and anchor
CHCH-TV's 11:00 p.m. news  package, weeknights, a post she commands to
this day.

<P> Not one to rest on her laurels, the multi-talented
Jennifer produced and hosted CHCH-TV's weekly travel  show, "Ontario
Adventures" during the summer of 1989 and 1990, while she was anchoring
the weekend  newscasts.  In addition, she has her own company, J.F.M.
Productions, which allows her to produce,  direct, write, and host a
variety of current affair programmes.  This endeavour complements
Jennifer's  strong belief in solid journalism, and her interests in the
environment, nature, history and economics.

<P>Jennifer Mossop is a
member of Canadian Women in Communications, and Toronto Women in Film
and  Television.  As well, she is always willing to share her free time
with many of the area's charitable  organizations.

<P> When not
working, Jennifer enjoys time with her musician husband, their long
haired dachshund, and  many family members and friends.  As well,
Jennifer takes pleasure in gardening, cooking, reading,  walking, and
music.  
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

